rdfs:label: implement traction source
IAO:0000115: Source of energy used to pulled an implement.

rdfs:label: role
IAO:0000115: A role is particular behaviour which a material entity may exhibit.

rdfs:label: collection of organisms
IAO:0000115: A material entity that consists of two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids.

rdfs:label: plant structure development stage
IAO:0000115: A stage in the life of a plant structure (PO:0009011) during which the plant structure undergoes developmental processes.

rdfs:label: sequentially ordered entity
IAO:0000115: Any entity that is ordered in discrete units along a linear axis.

rdfs:label: unit
IAO:0000115: A unit of measurement is a standardized quantity of a physical quality.

rdfs:label: experimental condition
IAO:0000115: A state of being, an external or environmental factor or a treatment observed or administered prior to or concurrent with an investigative procedure such as an assessment of a morphological or physiological state or property in a single individual or sample or in a group of individuals or samples, especially a state, factor or treatment which has the potential to influence the outcome of such an assessment.

rdfs:label: human power
IAO:0000115: A traction that uses only human power to use an implement.

rdfs:label: motorized traction
IAO:0000115: A traction that uses motorized power to pulled an implement.

rdfs:label: animal traction
IAO:0000115: A traction that uses animal power to pulled an implement.

rdfs:label: continuant
IAO:0000115: An entity that exists in full at any time in which it exists at all, persists through time while maintaining its identity and has no temporal parts.

rdfs:label: occurrent
IAO:0000115: An entity that has temporal parts and that happens, unfolds or develops through time.

rdfs:label: biological role
IAO:0000115: A role played by the molecular entity or part thereof within a biological context.

rdfs:label: application
IAO:0000115: Intended use of the molecular entity or part thereof by humans.

rdfs:label: chemical role
IAO:0000115: A role played by the molecular entity or part thereof within a chemical context.

rdfs:label: ecological community
IAO:0000115: A collection of organisms of at least two different species, living in a particular area.

rdfs:label: whole plant development stage
IAO:0000115: A plant structure development stage (PO:0009012) that has as primary participant a whole plant (PO:0000003).

rdfs:label: collective plant organ structure development stage
IAO:0000115: A plant structure development stage (PO:0009012) that has as primary participant a collective plant structure (PO:0025497).

rdfs:label: sequence atomic unit
IAO:0000115: Any individual unit of a collection of like units arranged in a linear order

rdfs:label: sequence bearer
IAO:0000115: Any entity that can be divided into parts such that each part is an atomical unit of a sequence

rdfs:label: base unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is one of a particular measure to which all measures of that type can be related.

rdfs:label: area unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of a 2-dimensional flat surface.

rdfs:label: speed/velocity unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the rate of movement. Speed is measured in the same physical units of measurement as velocity, but does not contain the element of direction that velocity has. Speed is thus the magnitude component of velocity.

rdfs:label: energy unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the work done by a certain force (gravitational, electric, magnetic, force of inertia, etc).

rdfs:label: angle unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the figure or space formed by the junction of two lines or planes.

rdfs:label: density unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the influence exerted by some mass.

rdfs:label: dimensionless unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of physical quantity consisting of only a numerical number without any units.

rdfs:label: electric potential difference unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the work done per unit charge as a charge is moved between two points in an electric field.

rdfs:label: replication
IAO:0000115: Replication is the repetition of the set of all the treatment combinations used in an experiment.

rdfs:label: experimental factor
IAO:0000115: A factor of an experiment is a controlled independent variable; a variable whose levels are set by the experimenter. A factor is a general type or category of treatments. Different treatments constitute different levels of a factor.

rdfs:label: experimental constraint
IAO:0000115: Constraint known to affect the experiment or the crop performances.

rdfs:label: complication during the experiment
IAO:0000115: Unexpected event arrived during the experiment.

rdfs:label: independent continuant
IAO:0000115: A continuant that is a bearer of quality and realizable entity entities, in which other entities inhere and which itself cannot inhere in anything.

rdfs:label: specifically dependent continuant
IAO:0000115: A continuant that inheres in or is borne by other entities. Every instance of A requires some specific instance of B which must always be the same.

rdfs:label: generically dependent continuant
IAO:0000115: A continuant that is dependent on one or other independent continuant bearers. For every instance of A requires some instance of (an independent continuant type) B but which instance of B serves can change from time to time.

rdfs:label: process
IAO:0000115: An occurrent that has temporal proper parts and for some time t, p s-depends_on some material entity at t.

rdfs:label: inhibitor
IAO:0000115: A substance that diminishes the rate of a chemical reaction.

rdfs:label: biochemical role
IAO:0000115: A biological role played by the molecular entity or part thereof within a biochemical context.

rdfs:label: aetiopathogenetic role
IAO:0000115: A role played by the molecular entity or part thereof which causes the development of a pathological process.

rdfs:label: poison
IAO:0000115: Any substance that causes disturbance to organisms by chemical reaction or other activity on the molecular scale, when a sufficient quantity is absorbed by the organism.

rdfs:label: pesticide
IAO:0000115: Strictly, a substance intended to kill pests. In common usage, any substance used for controlling, preventing, or destroying animal, microbiological or plant pests.

rdfs:label: agrochemical
IAO:0000115: An agrochemical is a substance that is used in agriculture or horticulture.

rdfs:label: reagent
IAO:0000115: A substance used in a chemical reaction to detect, measure, examine, or produce other substances.

rdfs:label: solvent
IAO:0000115: A liquid that can dissolve other substances (solutes) without any change in their chemical composition.

rdfs:label: pharmaceutical
IAO:0000115: Any substance introduced into a living organism with therapeutic or diagnostic purpose.

rdfs:label: food additive
IAO:0000115: Any substance which is added to food to preserve or enhance its flavour and/or appearance.

rdfs:label: propellant
IAO:0000115: A compressed gas or liquid with a boiling point lower than room temperature which to used to propel and dispense liquids such as deodorants, insecticides, paints, etc. from aerosol cans.

rdfs:label: refrigerant
IAO:0000115: A substance used in a thermodynamic heat pump cycle or refrigeration cycle that undergoes a phase change from a gas to a liquid and back. Refrigerants are used in air-conditioning systems and freezers or refrigerators and are assigned a "R" number (by ASHRAE - formerly the American Society of Heating, Refrigerating and Air Conditioning Engineers), which is determined systematically according to their molecular structure.

rdfs:label: acceptor
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity that can accept an electron, a pair of electrons, an atom or a group from another molecular entity.

rdfs:label: donor
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity that can transfer ("donate") an electron, a pair of electrons, an atom or a group to another molecular entity.

rdfs:label: base
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity having an available pair of electrons capable of forming a covalent bond with a hydron (Bronsted base) or with the vacant orbital of some other molecular entity (Lewis base).

rdfs:label: catalyst
IAO:0000115: A substance that increases the rate of a reaction without modifying the overall standard Gibbs energy change in the reaction.

rdfs:label: acid
IAO:0000115: An acid is a molecular entity capable of donating a hydron (Bronsted acid) or capable of forming a covalent bond with an electron pair (Lewis acid).

rdfs:label: oxidising agent
IAO:0000115: A substance that removes electrons from another reactant in a redox reaction.

rdfs:label: explosive
IAO:0000115: A substance capable of undergoing rapid and highly exothermic decomposition.

rdfs:label: greenhouse gas
IAO:0000115: A gas in an atmosphere that absorbs and emits radiation within the thermal infrared range, so contributing to the 'greenhouse effect'.

rdfs:label: life of whole plant stage
IAO:0000115: A maximal whole plant development stage.

rdfs:label: sporophyte development stage
IAO:0000115: A whole plant development stage (PO:0007033) that has as primary participant a whole plant (PO:0000003) during the interval between fertilization (or apogamy) and death.

rdfs:label: shoot system development stage
IAO:0000115: A collective plant organ structure development stage (PO:0025338) that begins with the onset of the plant organ development stage (PO:0025339) and ends with either gametophyte senescent stage (PO:0025343) or sporophyte senescent stage (PO:0007017) or death.

rdfs:label: square meter
IAO:0000115: An area unit which is equal to an area enclosed by a square with sides each 1 meter long.

rdfs:label: square centimeter
IAO:0000115: An area unit which is equal to one ten thousandth of a square meter or 10^[-4] m^[2].

rdfs:label: meter per second
IAO:0000115: A speed/velocity unit which is equal to the speed of an object traveling 1 meter distance in one second.

rdfs:label: watt-hour
IAO:0000115: An energy unit which is equal to the amount of electrical energy equivalent to a one-watt load drawing power for one hour.

rdfs:label: kilowatt-hour
IAO:0000115: An energy unit which is equal to 1,000 watt-hours.

rdfs:label: plane angle unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the angle formed by two straight lines in the same plane.

rdfs:label: mass density unit
IAO:0000115: A density unit which is a standard measure of the mass of a substance in a given volume.

rdfs:label: area density unit
IAO:0000115: A density unit which is a standard measure of the mass exerting an influence on a given area.

rdfs:label: linear density unit
IAO:0000115: A density unit which is a standard measure of the mass exerting an influence on a one-dimensional object.

rdfs:label: ratio
IAO:0000115: A dimensionless unit which denotes an amount or magnitude of one quantity relative to another.

rdfs:label: volt
IAO:0000115: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to the work per unit charge. One volt is the potential difference required to move one coulomb of charge between two points in a circuit while using one joule of energy.

rdfs:label: megavolt
IAO:0000115: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one million volts or 10^[6] V.

rdfs:label: equipement complication
IAO:0000115: A complication with the equipement used during the experiment.

rdfs:label: personel complication
IAO:0000115: A complication with a person or a group of people working on the experiement.

rdfs:label: flood
IAO:0000115: An unusual accumulation of water above the ground caused by high tide, heavy rain, melting snow or rapid runoff from paved areas.

rdfs:label: wildfire
IAO:0000115: A conflagration which is uncontrolled and combusts material in a vegetated area, be it rural or wild.

rdfs:label: drought
IAO:0000115: A hydrological precipitation process with a reduced rate relative to some historical average, typically resulting in ecosystemic perturbations.

rdfs:label: material entity
IAO:0000115: An independent continuant that is spatially extended whose identity is independent of that of other entities and can be maintained through time.

rdfs:label: anatomical entity
IAO:0000115: Biological entity that is either an individual member of a biological species or constitutes the structural organization of an individual member of a biological species.

rdfs:label: realizable entity
IAO:0000115: A specifically dependent continuant  that inheres in continuant  entities and are not exhibited in full at every time in which it inheres in an entity or group of entities. The exhibition or actualization of a realizable entity is a particular manifestation, functioning or process that occurs under certain circumstances.

rdfs:label: quality
IAO:0000115: A dependent entity that inheres in a bearer by virtue of how the bearer is related to other entities

rdfs:label: information content entity
IAO:0000115: A generically dependent continuant that is about some thing.

rdfs:label: environmental system process
IAO:0000115: A process in which includes the components of an environmental system as participants.

rdfs:label: biological_process
IAO:0000115: Any process specifically pertinent to the functioning of integrated living units: cells, tissues, organs, and organisms. A process is a collection of molecular events with a defined beginning and end.

rdfs:label: planned process
IAO:0000115: A processual entity that realizes a plan which is the concretization of a plan specification.

rdfs:label: planning
IAO:0000115: a process of creating or modifying a plan specification

rdfs:label: exposure event or process
IAO:0000115: A process occurring within or in the vicinity of an organism that exerts some causal influence on the organism via the interaction between an exposure stimulus and an exposure receptor. The exposure stimulus may be a process, material entity or condition (for example, lack of nutrients). The exposure receptor can be an organism, organism population or a part of an organism.

rdfs:label: signalling molecule
IAO:0000115: A molecular messenger in which the molecule is specifically involved in transmitting information between cells. Such molecules are released from the cell sending the signal, cross over the gap between cells by diffusion, and interact with specific receptors in another cell, triggering a response in that cell by activating a series of enzyme controlled reactions which lead to changes inside the cell.

rdfs:label: enzyme inhibitor
IAO:0000115: A compound or agent that combines with an enzyme in such a manner as to prevent the normal substrate-enzyme combination and the catalytic reaction.

rdfs:label: metabolite
IAO:0000115: Any intermediate or product resulting from metabolism. The term 'metabolite' subsumes the classes commonly known as primary and secondary metabolites.

rdfs:label: genotoxin
IAO:0000115: A role played by a chemical compound to induce direct or indirect DNA damage. Such damage can potentially lead to the formation of a malignant tumour, but DNA damage does not lead inevitably to the creation of cancerous cells.

rdfs:label: neurotoxin
IAO:0000115: A poison that interferes with the functions of the nervous system.

rdfs:label: food component
IAO:0000115: Any substance that is distributed in foodstuffs. It includes materials derived from plants or animals, such as vitamins or minerals, as well as environmental contaminants.

rdfs:label: fertilizer
IAO:0000115: A fertilizer is any substance that is added to soil or water to assist the growth of plants.

rdfs:label: bleaching agent
IAO:0000115: A reagent that lightens or whitens a substrate through chemical reaction. Bleaching reactions usually involve oxidative or reductive processes that degrade colour systems. Bleaching can occur by destroying one or more of the double bonds in the conjugated chain, by cleaving the conjugated chain, or by oxidation of one of the other moieties in the conjugated chain. Their reactivity results in many bleaches having strong bactericidal, disinfecting, and sterilising properties.

rdfs:label: nucleophilic reagent
IAO:0000115: A reagent that forms a bond to its reaction partner (the electrophile) by donating both bonding electrons.

rdfs:label: polar solvent
IAO:0000115: A solvent that is composed of polar molecules. Polar solvents can dissolve ionic compounds or ionisable covalent compounds.

rdfs:label: drug
IAO:0000115: Any substance which when absorbed into a living organism may modify one or more of its functions. The term is generally accepted for a substance taken for a therapeutic purpose, but is also commonly used for abused substances.

rdfs:label: food acidity regulator
IAO:0000115: A food additive that is used to change or otherwise control the acidity or alkalinity of foods. They may be acids, bases, neutralising agents or buffering agents.

rdfs:label: flour treatment agent
IAO:0000115: A food additive which is added to flour or dough to improve baking quality and/or colour.

rdfs:label: food packaging gas
IAO:0000115: A food additive that is a (generally inert) gas which is used to envelop foodstuffs during packing and so protect them from unwanted chemical reactions such as food spoilage or oxidation during subsequent transport and storage. The term includes propellant gases, used to expel foods from a container.

rdfs:label: food propellant
IAO:0000115: A propellant that is used to expel foods from an aerosol container.

rdfs:label: Bronsted base
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity capable of accepting a hydron from a donor (Bronsted acid).

rdfs:label: Bronsted acid
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity capable of donating a hydron to an acceptor (Bronsted base).

rdfs:label: Lewis base
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity able to provide a pair of electrons and thus capable of forming a covalent bond with an electron-pair acceptor (Lewis acid), thereby producing a Lewis adduct.

rdfs:label: bud development stage
IAO:0000115: A shoot system development stage (PO:0025527) that has as primary participant a bud (PO:0009006).

rdfs:label: reproductive shoot system development stage
IAO:0000115: A shoot system development stage (PO:0025527) that has as primary participant a reproductive shoot system (PO:0025082).

rdfs:label: degree
IAO:0000115: A plane angle unit which is equal to 1/360 of a full rotation or 1.7453310^[-2] rad.

rdfs:label: kilogram per cubic meter
IAO:0000115: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in kilograms divided by the volume in cubic meters.

rdfs:label: kilogram per liter
IAO:0000115: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in kilograms divided by the volume in liters.

rdfs:label: gram per liter
IAO:0000115: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in grams divided by the volume in liters.

rdfs:label: kilogram per square meter
IAO:0000115: An area density unit which is equal to the mass of an object in kilograms divided by the surface area in meters squared.

rdfs:label: kilogram per hectare
IAO:0000115: An area density unit which is equal to the mass of an object in kilograms divided by the surface area in hectares.

rdfs:label: ton per hectare
IAO:0000115: An area density unit which is equal to the mass of an object in tons divided by the surface area in hectares.

rdfs:label: kilogram per meter
IAO:0000115: An area density unit which is equal to the mass of an object in kilograms divided by one meter.

rdfs:label: percent
IAO:0000115: A dimensionless ratio unit which denotes numbers as fractions of 100.

rdfs:label: toxin
IAO:0000115: Poisonous substance produced by a biological organism such as a microbe, animal or plant.

rdfs:label: chemical entity
IAO:0000115: A chemical entity is a physical entity of interest in chemistry including molecular entities, parts thereof, and chemical substances.

rdfs:label: subatomic particle
IAO:0000115: A particle smaller than an atom.

rdfs:label: environmental feature
IAO:0000115: A material entity which determines an environmental system.

rdfs:label: environmental material
IAO:0000115: A portion of environmental material is a fiat object which forms the medium or part of the medium of an environmental system.

rdfs:label: meteor
IAO:0000115: A meteor is any matter- or energy-based entity which is located in the atmosphere of an astronomical body.

rdfs:label: material information bearer
IAO:0000115: A material entity in which a concretization of an information content entity inheres.

rdfs:label: processed material
IAO:0000115: Is a material entity that is created or changed during material processing.

rdfs:label: organization
IAO:0000115: An entity that can bear roles, has members, and has a set of organization rules. Members of organizations are either organizations themselves or individual people. Members can bear specific organization member roles that are determined in the organization rules. The organization rules also determine how decisions are made on behalf of the organization by the organization members.

rdfs:label: manufacturer
IAO:0000115: A person or organization that has a manufacturer role

rdfs:label: collection of specimens
IAO:0000115: A material entity that has two or more specimens as its parts.

rdfs:label: organism
IAO:0000115: A material entity that is an individual living system, such as animal, plant, bacteria or virus, that is capable of replicating or reproducing, growth and maintenance in the right environment. An organism may be unicellular or made up, like humans, of many billions of cells divided into specialized tissues and organs.

rdfs:label: specimen
IAO:0000115: A material entity that has the specimen role.

rdfs:label: material to be added
IAO:0000115: a material that is added to another one in a material combination process

rdfs:label: target of material addition
IAO:0000115: A material entity into which another is being added in a material combinatino process

rdfs:label: plant anatomical entity
IAO:0000115: An anatomical entity that is or was part of a plant.

rdfs:label: system
IAO:0000115: A material entity consisting of multiple components that are causally integrated.

rdfs:label: material anatomical entity
IAO:0000115: Anatomical entity that has mass.

rdfs:label: role
IAO:0000115: A realizable entity  the manifestation of which brings about some result or end that is not essential to a continuant  in virtue of the kind of thing that it is but that can be served or participated in by that kind of continuant  in some kinds of natural, social or institutional contexts.

rdfs:label: information carrier
IAO:0000115: A quality of an information bearer that imparts the information content

rdfs:label: morphology
IAO:0000115: A quality of a single physical entity inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's size or shape or structure.

rdfs:label: mass
IAO:0000115: A physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the proportion of the bearer's amount of matter.

rdfs:label: quality of a single physical entity
IAO:0000115: A physical object quality which inheres in a single-bearer.

rdfs:label: process quality
IAO:0000115: A quality which inheres in an process.

rdfs:label: physical object quality
IAO:0000115: A quality which inheres in a continuant.

rdfs:label: datum label
IAO:0000115: A label is a symbol that is part of some other datum and is used to either partially define  the denotation of that datum or to provide a means for identifying the datum as a member of the set of data with the same label

rdfs:label: data item
IAO:0000115: a data item is an information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.

rdfs:label: directive information entity
IAO:0000115: An information content entity whose concretizations indicate to their bearer how to realize them in a process.

rdfs:label: figure
IAO:0000115: An information content entity consisting of a two dimensional arrangement of information content entities such that the arrangement itself is about something.

rdfs:label: document
IAO:0000115: A collection of information content entities intended to be understood together as a whole

rdfs:label: conclusion based on data
IAO:0000115: An information content entity that is inferred from data.

rdfs:label: value specification
IAO:0000115: An information content entity that specifies a value within a classification scheme or on a quantitative scale.

rdfs:label: soil degradation
IAO:0000115: Soil degradation is a process which results in a change in soil health status resulting in a diminished capacity of the ecosystem in which the soil occurs to provide goods and services for its  beneficiaries.

rdfs:label: radiation
IAO:0000115: A process during which energy is emitted or transmitted in the form of waves or particles through space or a material medium.

rdfs:label: desertification
IAO:0000115: a type of land degradation in which a relatively dry land region becomes increasingly arid, typically losing its bodies of water as well as vegetation and wildlife.

rdfs:label: atmospheric process
IAO:0000115: A process which occurs within an atmosphere.

rdfs:label: anthropogenic environmental process
IAO:0000115: An environmental process which is driven by the action of humans.

rdfs:label: material accumulation process
IAO:0000115: A process during which the mass of one or more materials, present within a given site, increases.

rdfs:label: material transport process
IAO:0000115: A process during which material is displaced from it's original location and transported either to a new location or back to the original location.

rdfs:label: material transformation process
IAO:0000115: A process during which a portion of some environmental material is converted into a different material or a collection of materials.

rdfs:label: island formation process
IAO:0000115: A process which results in the formation of an island.

rdfs:label: disease course
IAO:0000115: The totality of all processes through which a given disease instance is realized.

rdfs:label: land levelling process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which the agricultural field surface is shaped for ensuring that the depths and discharge variations over the agricultural field are relatively uniform.

rdfs:label: crop residue management process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which the thickness of crop residue on the surface of an agricultural field is managed.

rdfs:label: irrigation process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which water is artificially supplied to plant or soil to sustain plants.

rdfs:label: pest control process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which unwanted organisms are controlled.

rdfs:label: harvesting process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which the useful part or parts of the plant are gathered.

rdfs:label: pruning process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which selected parts of the plant are removed. The practice entails targeted removal of diseased, damaged, dead, non-productive, structurally unsound, or otherwise unwanted tissue from plants. This is done in order to shape the plant or tree, improve plant or tree health, reduce the risk from falling branches, prepare nursery specimens for transplanting, and increase the yield or quality of harvested products.

rdfs:label: liming process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which a liming material is applied to soil to reduce acidity.

rdfs:label: plant transplanting process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which a plant is moved from one location to be planted in another one.

rdfs:label: planting process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which a plant reproductive material is set into the soil.

rdfs:label: treatment
IAO:0000115: A process during which some material is applied to a subject

rdfs:label: soil analysis process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which an analysis of soil is performed to determine soil characteristics.

rdfs:label: experiment
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which a procedure is carried out to support, refute, or validate a hypothesis.

rdfs:label: regulation of grazing
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which grazing animals on pasture are managed by humans.

rdfs:label: propping process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which a rigid support is used to support, or to prevent from falling a crop or a tree.

rdfs:label: agronomic fertilization process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which fertilizer is applied to an environmental material to promote the growth of a plant.

rdfs:label: crop cultivation process
IAO:0000115: A planned process during which the environment of a crop plant is maintained such that the plant grows

rdfs:label: documenting
IAO:0000115: a planned process in which a document is created or added to by including the specified input in it.

rdfs:label: investigation
IAO:0000115: a planned process that consists of parts: planning, study design execution, documentation and which produce conclusion(s).

rdfs:label: assay
IAO:0000115: A planned process with the objective to produce information about the material entity that is the evaluant, by physically examining it or its proxies.

rdfs:label: material processing
IAO:0000115: A planned process which results in physical changes in a specified input material

rdfs:label: drawing a conclusion based on data
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which data gathered in an investigation is evaluated in the context of existing knowledge with the objective to generate more general conclusions or to conclude that the data does not allow one to draw general conclusion

rdfs:label: study design execution
IAO:0000115: a planned process that carries out a study design

rdfs:label: specimen collection process
IAO:0000115: A planned process with the objective of collecting a specimen.

rdfs:label: study intervention
IAO:0000115: the part of the execution of an intervention design study which is varied between two or more subjects in the study

rdfs:label: training process
IAO:0000115: a process that achieves a training objective

rdfs:label: data transformation
IAO:0000115: A planned process that produces output data from input data.

rdfs:label: data visualization
IAO:0000115: An planned process that creates images, diagrams or animations from the input data.

rdfs:label: EC 3.* (hydrolase) inhibitor
IAO:0000115: Any enzyme inhibitor that interferes with the action of a hydrolase (EC 3.*.*.*).

rdfs:label: eukaryotic metabolite
IAO:0000115: Any  metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in eukaryotes, the taxon that include members of the fungi, plantae and animalia kingdoms.

rdfs:label: prokaryotic metabolite
IAO:0000115: Any metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in prokaryotes, the taxon that include members of domains such as the bacteria and archaea.

rdfs:label: nutrient
IAO:0000115: A nutrient is a food component that an organism uses to survive and grow.

rdfs:label: organic fertilizer
IAO:0000115: A fertilizer that is derived from animal or vegetable matter, and contains a carbon-hydrogen linkage.

rdfs:label: inorganic fertilizer
IAO:0000115: A fertilizer that does not contain a carbon-hydrogen linkage.

rdfs:label: protic solvent
IAO:0000115: A polar solvent that is capable of acting as a hydron (proton) donor.

rdfs:label: cardiovascular drug
IAO:0000115: A drug that affects the rate or intensity of cardiac contraction, blood vessel diameter or blood volume.

rdfs:label: astringent
IAO:0000115: A compound that causes the contraction of body tissues, typically used to reduce bleeding from minor abrasions.

rdfs:label: inorganic acid
IAO:0000115: A Bronsted acid derived from one or more inorganic compounds. Inorganic acids (also known as mineral acids) form hydrons and conjugate base ions when dissolved in water.

rdfs:label: weather station
IAO:0000115: An observation post where weather conditions and meteorological data are observed and recorded and reported.

rdfs:label: molecular entity
IAO:0000115: Any constitutionally or isotopically distinct atom, molecule, ion, ion pair, radical, radical ion, complex, conformer etc., identifiable as a separately distinguishable entity.

rdfs:label: group
IAO:0000115: A defined linked collection of atoms or a single atom within a molecular entity.

rdfs:label: atom
IAO:0000115: A chemical entity constituting the smallest component of an element having the chemical properties of the element.

rdfs:label: chemical substance
IAO:0000115: A chemical substance is a portion of matter of constant composition, composed of molecular entities of the same type or of different types.

rdfs:label: fundamental particle
IAO:0000115: A particle not known to have substructure.

rdfs:label: fermion
IAO:0000115: Particle of half-integer spin quantum number following Fermi-Dirac statistics. Fermions are named after Enrico Fermi.

rdfs:label: composite particle
IAO:0000115: A subatomic particle known to have substructure (i.e. consisting of smaller particles).

rdfs:label: nuclear particle
IAO:0000115: A nucleus or any of its constituents in any of their energy states.

rdfs:label: Vegetation maintained on an experimental field
IAO:0000115: Vegetation maintained in purpose on and at the border of an agronomic experimental field.

rdfs:label: vegetation surronding an experimental site
IAO:0000115: Type of vegetation surrounding an agronomic experimental site

rdfs:label: glacial feature
IAO:0000115: A hydrographic feature characterized by the dominance of snow or ice.

rdfs:label: mesoscopic physical object
IAO:0000115: An environmental feature that is, or can be, contained and is predominantly composed of one or a few types of stuff.

rdfs:label: environmental zone
IAO:0000115: An environmental zone is an environmental feature whose extent is determined by the presence or influence of one or more material entities or processes. An environmental zone may, itself, assume the role of an environmental feature.

rdfs:label: outer space
IAO:0000115: Outer space is a hard vacuum containing a low density of particles, predominantly a plasma of hydrogen and helium as well as electromagnetic radiation, magnetic fields, neutrinos, dust and cosmic rays that exists between celestial bodies.

rdfs:label: astronomical object
IAO:0000115: An object which is composed of one or more gravitationally bound structures that are associated with a position in space.

rdfs:label: astronomical body part
IAO:0000115: A material part of an astronomical body.

rdfs:label: green manure
IAO:0000115: Plants that are grown to be tilled, or cut down to lay on top of the ground for the purpose of adding organic matter and nutrients to the soil.

rdfs:label: animal manure
IAO:0000115: Organic matter mostly derived from animal feces which can be used as organic fertilizer in agriculture.

rdfs:label: oil cake
IAO:0000115: The biomass remaining after pressing oil seeds to extract oil.

rdfs:label: blood meal
IAO:0000115: Dry, inert powder made from blood. Blood usually comes from cattle or hogs as a slaughterhouse by-product.

rdfs:label: oil meal
IAO:0000115: An agricultural environmental material that contains ground-biomass remaining after pressing oil seeds.

rdfs:label: alfalfa meal
IAO:0000115: An agricultural environmental material that contains ground dry alfalfa.

rdfs:label: mulch
IAO:0000115: Layer of material applied to the soil surface to conserve moisture, improve soil fertility, reduce weed growth, or enhance the visual appeal of the area.

rdfs:label: liming material
IAO:0000115: An environmental material containing calcium and/or magnesium compounds  and applied to soil in order to neutralize soil acidity.

rdfs:label: scree
IAO:0000115: Broken rock that appears at the bottom of crags, mountain cliffs or valley shoulders.

rdfs:label: soil
IAO:0000115: Soil is an environmental material which is primarily composed of minerals, varying proportions of sand, silt, and clay, organic material such as humus, gases, liquids, and a broad range of resident micro- and macroorganisms.

rdfs:label: waste material
IAO:0000115: A material which is not the desired output of a process and which is typically the input of a process which removes it from its producer (e.g. a disposal process).

rdfs:label: clay
IAO:0000115: A group of hydrous aluminium phyllosilicate (phyllosilicates being a subgroup of silicate minerals) minerals (see clay minerals), that are typically less than 2 micrometres in diameter. Clay consists of a variety of phyllosilicate minerals rich in silicon and aluminium oxides and hydroxides which include variable amounts of structural water.

rdfs:label: anthropogenic environmental material
IAO:0000115: Anthropogenic material in or on which organisms may live.

rdfs:label: silt
IAO:0000115: Silt is granular material of a size somewhere between sand and clay whose mineral origin is quartz and feldspar.

rdfs:label: sand
IAO:0000115: A naturally occurring granular material composed of finely divided rock and mineral particles.

rdfs:label: gravel
IAO:0000115: Gravel is an environmental material which is composed of pieces of rock that are at least two millimeters (2mm) in its largest dimension and no more than 75 millimeters.

rdfs:label: particulate matter
IAO:0000115: Particulate material is an environmental material which is composed of microscopic portions of solid or liquid material suspended in another environmental material.

rdfs:label: organic material
IAO:0000115: Environmental material derived from living organisms.

rdfs:label: lava
IAO:0000115: Lava is a mixture of molten or semi-molten rock, volatiles, and solids which has extruded beyond a planetary crust.

rdfs:label: magma
IAO:0000115: Magma is a mixture of molten or semi-molten rock, volatiles, and solids that is found beneath the uppermost solid layer of a planetary body. Besides molten rock, magma may also contain suspended crystals, dissolved gas and sometimes gas bubbles.

rdfs:label: tephra
IAO:0000115: Tephra is fragmental material produced by a volcanic eruption regardless of composition, fragment size or emplacement mechanism.

rdfs:label: gaseous environmental material
IAO:0000115: A material entity which is composed of one or more chemical entities and has neither independent shape nor volume but tends to expand indefinitely.

rdfs:label: marl
IAO:0000115: Marl is a mass of calcium carbonate derived from mollusk shells and mixed with silt and clay.

rdfs:label: metallic material
IAO:0000115: A material which is composed primarily of one or more pure metals and which shows their properties.

rdfs:label: ice
IAO:0000115: An ice is an environmental material which is either frozen or which is maintained in a solid state by gravitational forces or pressure.

rdfs:label: volatile astrogeological material
IAO:0000115: A material which is composed primarily of chemical elements and compounds with relatively low boiling points, equilibrium condensation temperatures below 1300 Kelvin, and which are part of the crust or atmosphere of a moon or planet.

rdfs:label: hydrometeor
IAO:0000115: A meteor which is primarily composed of water.

rdfs:label: lithometeor
IAO:0000115: A meteor which is primarily composed of rock.

rdfs:label: processed specimen
IAO:0000115: A specimen that has been intentionally physically modified.

rdfs:label: regulatory agency
IAO:0000115: A regulatory agency is a organization that has responsibility over or for  the legislation (acts and regulations) for a given sector of the government.

rdfs:label: research organization
IAO:0000115: An organization formed with a goal to have its members conduct investigations

rdfs:label: grant agency
IAO:0000115: An organization that provides funding support for projects such as investigations.

rdfs:label: draft animal
IAO:0000115: Organism used to pull agricultural implements.

rdfs:label: crop
IAO:0000115: A crop is any cultivated plant, fungus, or alga that is harvested for food, clothing, livestock,fodder, biofuel, medicine, or other uses

rdfs:label: selectively maintained organism
IAO:0000115: An organism that is bred to have some uniform behavioral, morphological, physiological, or genetic characteristics with similarly bred organisms

rdfs:label: plant reproductive material
IAO:0000115: A plant anatomical entity that is defined to mean plants or parts of plant capable of and intended for producing or reproducing entire plants.

rdfs:label: plant structure
IAO:0000115: An anatomical structure that is or was part of a plant, or was derived from a part of a plant.

rdfs:label: environmental system
IAO:0000115: A system which has the disposition to environ one or more material entities.

rdfs:label: disease
IAO:0000115: A disposition (i) to undergo pathological processes that (ii) exists in an organism because of one or more disorders in that organism.

rdfs:label: irrigation water source role
IAO:0000115: A role that inheres in a water body that is realised in an irrigation process where water is transported from that water body to the target of the irrigation process.

rdfs:label: pest role
IAO:0000115: A role that inheres in an organism that is realized in an agricultural process where the organism is unwanted.

rdfs:label: biological pest control agent role
IAO:0000115: A role that inheres in an organism that is realised in a pest control process where that organism is used to suppress unwanted organisms.

rdfs:label: liming role
IAO:0000115: A role that inheres in an environmental material that is realised in a land preparation process where that environmental material is applied to soil in order to neutralize soil acidity.

rdfs:label: person role within the experiment
IAO:0000115: Roled performed by a person during an experiment.

rdfs:label: waste role
IAO:0000115: A role that is realized in some process wherein the bearer is discarded or not utilized further.

rdfs:label: regulatory role
IAO:0000115: a role which inheres in material entities and is realized in the processes of making, enforcing or being defined by legislation or orders issued by a governmental body.

rdfs:label: evaluant role
IAO:0000115: a role that inheres in a material entity that is realized in an assay in which data is generated about the bearer of the evaluant role

rdfs:label: specimen role
IAO:0000115: a role borne by a material entity that is gained during a specimen collection process and that can be realized by use of the specimen in an investigation

rdfs:label: investigation agent role
IAO:0000115: A role borne by an entity and that is realized in a process that is part of an investigation in which an objective is achieved. These processes include, among others: planning, overseeing, funding, reviewing.

rdfs:label: material to be added role
IAO:0000115: material to be added role is a protocol participant role realized by a material which is added into a material bearing the target of material addition role in a material addition process

rdfs:label: target of material addition role
IAO:0000115: target of material addition role is a role realized by an entity into which a material is added in a material addition process

rdfs:label: manufacturer role
IAO:0000115: Manufacturer role is a role which inheres in a person or organization and which is realized by a manufacturing process.

rdfs:label: service provider role
IAO:0000115: is a role which inheres in a person or organization and is realized in in a planned process which provides access to training, materials or execution of protocols for an organization or person

rdfs:label: shape
IAO:0000115: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ratios of distances between its features (points, edges, surfaces and also holes etc).

rdfs:label: size
IAO:0000115: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's physical magnitude.

rdfs:label: structure
IAO:0000115: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's relative position, shape, arrangements and connectivity of an organism's various parts; the pattern underlying its form.

rdfs:label: amorphous
IAO:0000115: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lack of distinct morphology.

rdfs:label: age
IAO:0000115: A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of how long the bearer has existed.

rdfs:label: behavioral quality
IAO:0000115: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's behavior aggregate of the responses or reactions or movements in a given situation.

rdfs:label: intensity
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's possessing or displaying a distinctive feature in type or degree or effect or force.

rdfs:label: deviation(from_normal)
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the whether the bearer differs from normal or average.

rdfs:label: amount
IAO:0000115: The number of entities of this type that are part of the whole organism.

rdfs:label: physical quality
IAO:0000115: A quality of a physical entity that exists through action of continuants at the physical level of organisation in relation to other entities.

rdfs:label: has number of
IAO:0000115: The number of parts of a particular type that the bearer entity has. This is a relational quality, and thus holds between two entities: the bearer of the quality, and the type of parts.

rdfs:label: organismal quality
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an entire organism or part of an organism.

rdfs:label: molecular quality
IAO:0000115: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity, a single molecule, atom, ion, radical etc.

rdfs:label: decreased object quality
IAO:0000115: A quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

rdfs:label: increased object quality
IAO:0000115: A quality of an object that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

rdfs:label: measurement unit label
IAO:0000115: A measurement unit label is as a label that is part of a scalar measurement datum and denotes a unit of measure.

rdfs:label: categorical label
IAO:0000115: A label that is part of a categorical datum and that indicates the value of the data item on the categorical scale.

rdfs:label: data set
IAO:0000115: A data item that is an aggregate of other data items of the same type that have something in common. Averages and distributions can be determined for data sets.

rdfs:label: data about an ontology part
IAO:0000115: data about an ontology part is a data item about a part of an ontology, for example a term

rdfs:label: measurement datum
IAO:0000115: A measurement datum is an information content entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement such as produced by a device.

rdfs:label: center value
IAO:0000115: A data item that is produced as the output of a center calculation data transformation and represents the center value of the input data.

rdfs:label: average value
IAO:0000115: A  data item that is produced as the output of an averaging data transformation and represents the average value of the input data.

rdfs:label: objective specification
IAO:0000115: a directive information entity that describes an intended process endpoint. When part of a plan specification the concretization is realized in a planned process in which the bearer tries to effect the world so that the process endpoint is achieved.

rdfs:label: action specification
IAO:0000115: a directive information entity that describes an action the bearer will take

rdfs:label: data format specification
IAO:0000115:
A data format specification is the information content borne by the document published defining the specification.
Example: The ISO document specifying what encompasses an XML document; The instructions in a XSD file

rdfs:label: plan specification
IAO:0000115: A directive information entity with action specifications and objective specifications as parts that, when concretized, is realized in a process in which the bearer tries to achieve the objectives by taking the actions specified.

rdfs:label: study design independent variable
IAO:0000115: a directive information entity that is part of a study design. Independent variables are entities whose values are selected to determine its relationship to an observed phenomenon (the dependent variable). In such an experiment, an attempt is made to find evidence that the values of the independent variable determine the values of the dependent variable (that which is being measured). The independent variable can be changed as required, and its values do not represent a problem requiring explanation in an analysis, but are taken simply as given. The dependent variable on the other hand, usually cannot be directly controlled

rdfs:label: dose specification
IAO:0000115: a directive information entity that describes the dose that will be administered to a target

rdfs:label: image
IAO:0000115: An image is an affine projection to a two dimensional surface, of measurements of some quality of an entity or entities repeated at regular intervals across a spatial range, where the measurements are represented as color and luminosity on the projected on surface.

rdfs:label: diagram
IAO:0000115: A figure that expresses one or more propositions

rdfs:label: questionnaire
IAO:0000115: A document with a set of printed or written questions with a choice of answers, devised for the purposes of a survey or statistical study.

rdfs:label: categorical value specification
IAO:0000115: A value specification that is specifies one category out of a fixed number of nominal categories

rdfs:label: scalar value specification
IAO:0000115: A value specification that consists of two parts: a numeral and a unit label

rdfs:label: anthropisation
IAO:0000115: A process during which a natural environmental system is altered by human action.

rdfs:label: percolation process in soil
IAO:0000115: Hydrological process in which water move through soil and permeable rocks.

rdfs:label: volcanic eruption
IAO:0000115: A volcanic process is a process during which lava, tephra (ash, lapilli, volcanic bombs and blocks), and assorted gases are expelled from a volcanic vent or fissure.

rdfs:label: flooding
IAO:0000115: A general and temporary condition of partial or complete inundation of normally dry land areas from the overflow of inland and/or tidal waters, and/or the unusual and rapid accumulation or runoff of surface waters from any source. A great flow along a watercourse or a flow causing inundation of lands not normally covered by water.

rdfs:label: mass gaseous flow
IAO:0000115: A process whereby a large volume of gas moves due to a disequilibrium of physical forces.

rdfs:label: precipitation process
IAO:0000115: A precipitation process is a process in which a portion of some substance segregates from a material in which that substance or its precursors were dissolved or suspended in and settles due to a force such as gravity or centrifugal force.

rdfs:label: erosion
IAO:0000115: An action of exogenic processes (such as water flow or wind) which remove soil and rock from one location on the Earth's crust, then transport it to another location where it is deposited.

rdfs:label: aeolian transport process
IAO:0000115: A material transport process during which one or more environmental materials are transported by the action of wind.

rdfs:label: condensation process
IAO:0000115: Condensation is a process during which a gas undergoes a phase transition into a liquid.

rdfs:label: laser land levelling process
IAO:0000115: A land levelling process in which a laser guided equipement is used to shape land surface.

rdfs:label: traditional land levelling process
IAO:0000115: A land levelling process which uses animal drawn or tractor-drawn levelers.

rdfs:label: crop residue burning process
IAO:0000115: A crop residue management process in which crop residues are burned in the field.

rdfs:label: crop residue spreading process
IAO:0000115: A crop residue management process in which crop residues are spread across the field.

rdfs:label: tillage
IAO:0000115: group together tillage and no-till processes

rdfs:label: localized irrigation process
IAO:0000115: An irrigation process in which water is distributed under low pressure through a piped network, and is applied as a small discharge to each plant or adjacent to it.

rdfs:label: sprinkler irrigation process
IAO:0000115: An irrigation process in which water is distributed through a system of pipes, and is sprayed into the air through sprinklers so that it breaks up into small water drops which fall to the ground.

rdfs:label: sub-irrigation process
IAO:0000115: An irrigation process in which water is delivered to the plant root zone from below the soil surface.

rdfs:label: surface irrigation process
IAO:0000115: An irrigation process in which water is applied and distributed over the soil surface by gravity.

rdfs:label: mechanical pest control process
IAO:0000115: A pest control process in which physical means such as barriers, traps and handpicking, or physical conditions like high temperature, are used to control unwanted organisms.

rdfs:label: biological pest control process
IAO:0000115: A pest control process in which organisms are employed to manage unwanted organisms.

rdfs:label: chemical pest control process
IAO:0000115: A pest control process in which chemical is used to manage unwanted organisms.

rdfs:label: threshing process
IAO:0000115: Planned process is which the edible part of the cereal grain is loosen from the scaly, inedible chaff that surrounds it. It is the step in grain preparation after harvesting and before winnowing, which separates the loosened chaff from the grain. Threshing does not remove the bran from the grain.

rdfs:label: winnowing process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which the grain is separated from chaff. It is also used to remove weevils or other pests from stored grain. It is done after threshing, the loosening of grain or seeds from the husks and straw.

rdfs:label: desuckering process
IAO:0000115: A pruning process in which one or more suckers are removed.

rdfs:label: tree topping process
IAO:0000115: A pruning process in which whole tops of trees or large branches and/or trunks from the tops of trees are removed, leaving stubs or lateral branches that are too small to assume the role of a terminal leader.

rdfs:label: detrashing process
IAO:0000115: A pruning process in which dried, yellowish green, bottom leaves in the sugarcane crop are removed at regular intervals.

rdfs:label: seeding process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which seeds are applied on or into the soil.

rdfs:label: agricultural experiment
IAO:0000115: An experiment in which a scientific method is implemented for testing certain agricultural phenomena.

rdfs:label: rotational grazing
IAO:0000115: A grazing management system in which the land is subdivided or sectioned off into smaller areas, sometimes called paddocks. The livestock are moved from one paddock to another in order to best promote plant health and growth.

rdfs:label: continuous grazing
IAO:0000115: A grazing management system in which livestock have unrestricted access to the pasture area throughout the grazing season.

rdfs:label: handedness assay
IAO:0000115: A handedness assay measures the unequal distribution of fine motor skill between the left and right hands typically in human subjects by means of some questionnaire and scoring procedure.

rdfs:label: age measurement assay
IAO:0000115: An assay that measures the duration of temporal interval of a process that is part of the life of the bearer, where the initial time point of the measured process is the beginning of some transitional state of the bearer such as birth or when planted.

rdfs:label: manufacturing
IAO:0000115: Manufacturing is a process with the intent to produce a processed material which will have a function for future use. A person or organization (having manufacturer role) is a participant in this process

rdfs:label: material combination
IAO:0000115: is a material processing with the objective to combine two or more material entities as input into a single material entity as output.

rdfs:label: class prediction data transformation
IAO:0000115: A class prediction data transformation (sometimes called supervised classification) is a data transformation that has objective class prediction.

rdfs:label: decision tree building data transformation
IAO:0000115: A decision tree building data transformation is a data transformation that has objective decision tree induction.

rdfs:label: peak matching
IAO:0000115: Peak matching is a data transformation performed on a dataset of a graph of ordered data points (e.g. a spectrum) with the objective of pattern matching local maxima above a noise threshold

rdfs:label: averaging data transformation
IAO:0000115: An averaging data transformation is a data transformation that has objective averaging.

rdfs:label: partitioning data transformation
IAO:0000115: A partitioning data transformation is a data transformation that has objective partitioning.

rdfs:label: class discovery data transformation
IAO:0000115: A class discovery data transformation (sometimes called unsupervised classification) is a data transformation that has objective class discovery.

rdfs:label: center calculation data transformation
IAO:0000115: A center calculation data transformation is a data transformation that has objective of center calculation.

rdfs:label: clustered data visualization
IAO:0000115: A data visualization which has input of a clustered data set and produces an output of a report graph which is capable of rendering data of this type.

rdfs:label: EC 3.5.* (hydrolases acting on non-peptide C-N bonds) inhibitor
IAO:0000115: Any hydrolase inhibitor that interferes with the action of a hydrolase acting on C-N bonds, other than peptide bonds (EC 3.5.*.*).

rdfs:label: animal metabolite
IAO:0000115: Any eukaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in animals that include diverse creatures from sponges, insects to mammals.

rdfs:label: fungal metabolite
IAO:0000115: Any eukaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in fungi, the kingdom that includes microorganisms such as the yeasts and moulds.

rdfs:label: algal metabolite
IAO:0000115: Any eukaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in algae including unicellular organisms like chlorella and diatoms to multicellular organisms like giant kelps and brown algae.

rdfs:label: bacterial metabolite
IAO:0000115: Any prokaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in bacteria.

rdfs:label: micronutrient
IAO:0000115: Any nutrient required in small quantities by organisms throughout their life in order to orchestrate a range of physiological functions.

rdfs:label: vasodilator agent
IAO:0000115: A drug used to cause dilation of the blood vessels.

rdfs:label: length unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the distance between two points.

rdfs:label: mass unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of matter/energy of a physical object.

rdfs:label: time unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the dimension in which events occur in sequence.

rdfs:label: temperature unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the average kinetic energy of the particles in a sample of matter.

rdfs:label: concentration unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which represents a standard measurement of how much of a given substance there is mixed with another substance.

rdfs:label: volume unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of space occupied by any substance, whether solid, liquid, or gas.

rdfs:label: frequency unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the number of repetitive actions in a particular time.

rdfs:label: volumetric flow rate unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the volume of fluid which passes through a given surface per unit time .

rdfs:label: snow
IAO:0000115: Snow is an environmental material which is primarily composed of flakes of crystalline water ice.

rdfs:label: hydrological condensation process
IAO:0000115: Hydrological condensation is a process in which atmospheric water vapour undergoes a phase transition from the gas phase to the liquid phase.

rdfs:label: tractor
IAO:0000115: A mobile machine specifically designed to deliver a high tractive effort at slow speeds, and mainly used for the purposes of hauling a trailer or machinery used in agriculture or construction.

rdfs:label: land levelling implement
IAO:0000115: An implement that is used during a land levelling process.

rdfs:label: residue management implement
IAO:0000115: An implement that is used during a residue management process.

rdfs:label: fertilization implement
IAO:0000115: An implement that is used during a fertilization process.

rdfs:label: transplanting implement
IAO:0000115: An implement that is used during a transplanting process.

rdfs:label: planting implement
IAO:0000115: An implement that is used in a planting process.

rdfs:label: harvest implement
IAO:0000115: An implement that is used in an harvest process.

rdfs:label: mulch implement
IAO:0000115: An implement that is used during a mulch process.

rdfs:label: irrigation equipment
IAO:0000115: An equipment that is used during an irrigation process.

rdfs:label: isotopically modified compound
IAO:0000115: Any molecular entity in which the isotopic ratio of nuclides for at least one element deviates measurably from that occurring in nature. The term includes both isotopically substituted compounds (in which essentially all the molecules of the compound have only the indicated nuclide(s) at each designated position) and isotopically labeled compounds (a formal mixture of an isotopically unmodified compound with one or more analogous isotopically substituted compound(s).

rdfs:label: inorganic molecular entity
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity that contains no carbon.

rdfs:label: ion
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity having a net electric charge.

rdfs:label: elemental molecular entity
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity all atoms of which have the same atomic number.

rdfs:label: main group molecular entity
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity containing one or more atoms from any of groups 1, 2, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, and 18 of the periodic table.

rdfs:label: polyatomic entity
IAO:0000115: Any molecular entity consisting of more than one atom.

rdfs:label: inorganic group
IAO:0000115: Any substituent group which does not contain carbon.

rdfs:label: organic group
IAO:0000115: Any substituent group or skeleton containing carbon.

rdfs:label: metalloid atom
IAO:0000115: An atom of an element that exhibits properties that are between those of metals and nonmetals, or that has a mixture of them. The term generally includes boron, silicon, germanium, arsenic, antimony, and tellurium, while carbon, aluminium, selenium, polonium, and astatine are less commonly included.

rdfs:label: main group element atom
IAO:0000115: An atom belonging to one of the main groups (found in the s- and p- blocks) of the periodic table.

rdfs:label: metal atom
IAO:0000115: An atom of an element that exhibits typical metallic properties, being typically shiny, with high electrical and thermal conductivity.

rdfs:label: mixture
IAO:0000115: A mixture is a chemical substance composed of multiple molecules, at least two of which are of a different kind.

rdfs:label: lepton
IAO:0000115: Lepton is a fermion that does not experience the strong force (strong interaction). The term is derived from the Greek lambdaepsilonpitauomicronsigma (small, thin).

rdfs:label: baryon
IAO:0000115: Baryon is a fermion that does experience the strong force (strong interaction). The term is derived from the Greek betaalpharhoupsilonsigma (heavy).

rdfs:label: hadron
IAO:0000115: Hadron is a subatomic particle which experiences the strong force.

rdfs:label: atomic nucleus
IAO:0000115: A nucleus is the positively charged central portion of an atom, excluding the orbital electrons.

rdfs:label: flower strip
IAO:0000115: Strip of flowers established at the edge of the field.

rdfs:label: agricultural field
IAO:0000115: An area of land, usually relatively small, enclosed or otherwise and used for agricultural purposes.

rdfs:label: vegetated area
IAO:0000115: A vegetated area is a geographic feature which has ground cover dominated by plant communities.

rdfs:label: row
IAO:0000115: two or more crop plants planted in a line.

rdfs:label: interrow
IAO:0000115: A site which is located between two rows of crop plants.

rdfs:label: bund
IAO:0000115: Small earth embankment which contain irrigation water within basins.

rdfs:label: agricultural experimental plot
IAO:0000115: A site within which an agricultural experimental process is conducted

rdfs:label: block
IAO:0000115: A block is a relatively large area or several identical units receiving all or most of the treatments. A collection of plots is called a block.

rdfs:label: pot
IAO:0000115: A rounded container used to cultivate plant.

rdfs:label: experimental site
IAO:0000115: Location where the experiment is implemented.

rdfs:label: column
IAO:0000115: Vertical arrangement of plants in a field.

rdfs:label: field
IAO:0000115: An unbroken expanse (as of ice)

rdfs:label: rural area
IAO:0000115: An area which is outside of a town, city, or urban area. Rural areas are primarily used for agriculture or pastoralism and may contain rural settlements.

rdfs:label: astronomical body
IAO:0000115: An object which is naturally occuring, bound together by gravitational or electromagnetic forces, and surrounded by space.

rdfs:label: volcanic feature
IAO:0000115: A feature associated with a volcano, an opening, or rupture, in the Earth's surface or crust, which allows hot, molten rock, ash and gases to escape from deep below the surface.

rdfs:label: biosphere
IAO:0000115: A biosphere is an environmental system which includes, as parts, all the living entities within the gravitational sphere of influence of an astronomical body, and the non-living and dead entities which they interact with.

rdfs:label: hydrosphere
IAO:0000115: An astronomical body part which is composed of the combined mass of water found on, under, and over the surface of a planet.

rdfs:label: technosphere
IAO:0000115: An environmental system which includes, as parts, all the entities which have been constructed or manufactured by humans or their technology within the gravitational sphere of influence of an astronomical body.

rdfs:label: farmyard manure
IAO:0000115: Animal manure that contains plant material, which has been used as bedding for animals and has absorbed the feces and urine.

rdfs:label: farm slurry
IAO:0000115: An animal manure made of animal feces and urine with no or very little material used for animal bedding.

rdfs:label: liquid manure
IAO:0000115: An animal manure made of animal urine and sometimes waste water.

rdfs:label: poultry litter
IAO:0000115: An animal manure that contains poultry excreta, spilled feed, feathers, and material used as bedding in poultry operations.

rdfs:label: fish manure
IAO:0000115: An animal manure that contains solid waste from fishes often originateing from aquaculture operations.

rdfs:label: fish emulsion
IAO:0000115: An animal manure that is produced from ground-up whole fish or by-products mixed with water, and heated to remove oils and proteins.

rdfs:label: fish meal
IAO:0000115: An animal manure obtained by drying and grinding or otherwise treating fish or fish waste to which no other matter has been added.

rdfs:label: fish hydrolysate
IAO:0000115: An animal manure made from whole fish or by-products put into water and cold-ground up.

rdfs:label: cottonseed meal
IAO:0000115: An oil meal that contains crushed cotton seeds from which oil has been removed.

rdfs:label: plastic mulch
IAO:0000115: A mulch where plastic sheet is used to cover soil surface. Plants grow through slits or holes in thin plastic sheeting.

rdfs:label: landscape fabric
IAO:0000115: A mulch where textile material is used to covert the soil surface. The fabric itself can be made from synthetic or organic materials, sometimes from recycled sources.

rdfs:label: paper mulch
IAO:0000115: A mulch where shredded or entire piece of paper or newspaper cover the soil surface.

rdfs:label: grass clippings mulch
IAO:0000115: A mulch where lawnwaste resulting from mowing are used to cover the soil surface.

rdfs:label: pine needles mulch
IAO:0000115: A mulch where pine needles are used to cover soil surface.

rdfs:label: straw mulch
IAO:0000115: A mulch where straw is used to cover soil surface.

rdfs:label: aluminum mulch
IAO:0000115: A mulch where foil is used to cover soil surface.

rdfs:label: stone mulch
IAO:0000115: A mulch where stones are used to cover soil surface.

rdfs:label: leave mulch
IAO:0000115: A mulch where tree leaves are used to cover soil surface.

rdfs:label: compost mulch
IAO:0000115: A mulch where compost is used to cover soil surface.

rdfs:label: wood chips mulch
IAO:0000115: A mulch where wood chips are used to cover soil surface. Wood chipsare abyproductof the pruning of trees.

rdfs:label: bark mulch
IAO:0000115: A mulch where the outer corky bark layer of timber trees, shredded or not, are used to cover soil surface.

rdfs:label: calcium oxide
IAO:0000115: A member of the class of calcium oxides of calcium and oxygen in a 1:1 ratio.

rdfs:label: sludge
IAO:0000115: The residual semi-solid material left from domestic or industrial processes, or wastewater treatment processes.

rdfs:label: limestone
IAO:0000115: A sedimentary rock composed largely of the mineral calcite.

rdfs:label: permafrost
IAO:0000115: Soil at or below the freezing point of water (0C or 32F) for two or more years. Ice is not always present, as may be in the case of nonporous bedrock, but it frequently occurs and it may be in amounts exceeding the potential hydraulic saturation of the ground material.

rdfs:label: arenosol
IAO:0000115: Arenosols are sandy soils, including both soils developed in residual sands after in situ weathering of usually quartz-rich sediments or rock, and soils developed in recently deposited sands such as dunes in deserts and beach lands.

rdfs:label: andosol
IAO:0000115: Andosols are soils that develop in volcanic ejecta or glasses under almost any climate (except under hyperarid climate conditions). However, Andosols may also develop in other silicate-rich materials under acid weathering in humid and perhumid climates.

rdfs:label: acrisol
IAO:0000115: Acrisols are soils that have a higher clay content in the subsoil than in the topsoil as a result of pedogenetic processes (especially clay migration) leading to an argic subsoil horizon. Acrisols have in certain depths a low base saturation and low-activity clays.

rdfs:label: cambisol
IAO:0000115: Cambisols combine soils with at least an incipient subsurface soil formation. Transformation of parent material is evident from structure formation and mostly brownish discoloration, increasing clay percentage, and/or carbonate removal.

rdfs:label: chernozem
IAO:0000115: Chernozems are soils with a thick black surface layer that is rich in organic matter.

rdfs:label: kastanozem
IAO:0000115: Kastanozems are dry grassland soils, among them the zonal soils of the short-grass steppe belt, south of the Eurasian tall-grass steppe belt with Chernozems. Kastanozems have a similar profile to that of Chernozems but the humus-rich surface horizon is thinner and not as dark as that of the Chernozems and they show more prominent accumulation of secondary carbonates.

rdfs:label: histosol
IAO:0000115: Histosols comprise soils formed in organic material. These vary from soils developed in predominantly moss peat in boreal, arctic and subarctic regions, via moss peat, reeds/ sedge peat (fen) and forest peat in temperate regions to mangrove peat and swamp forest peat in the humid tropics. Histosols are found at all altitudes, but the vast majority occurs in lowlands.

rdfs:label: gleysol
IAO:0000115: Gleysols are wetland soils that, unless drained, are saturated with groundwater for long enough periods to develop a characteristic gleyic colour pattern. This pattern is essentially made up of reddish, brownish or yellowish colours at ped surfaces and/or in the upper soil layer or layers, in combination with greyish/bluish colours inside the peds and/or deeper in the soil.

rdfs:label: gypsisol
IAO:0000115: Gypsisols are soils with substantial secondary accumulation of gypsum (calcium sulfate). These soils are found in the driest parts of the arid climate zone.

rdfs:label: ferralsol
IAO:0000115: Ferralsols represent the classical, deeply weathered, red or yellow soils of the humid tropics. These soils have diffuse horizon boundaries, a clay assemblage dominated by low-activity clays (mainly kaolinite) and a high content of sesquioxides.

rdfs:label: nitisol
IAO:0000115: Nitisols are deep, well-drained, red, tropical soils with diffuse horizon boundaries and a subsurface horizon with more than 30 percent clay and moderate to strong angular blocky structure elements that easily fall apart into characteristic shiny, polyhedric (nutty) elements. Weathering is relatively advanced but Nitisols are far more productive than most other red, tropical soils.

rdfs:label: luvisol
IAO:0000115: Luvisols are soils that have a higher clay content in the subsoil than in the topsoil as a result of pedogenetic processes (especially clay migration) leading to an argic subsoil horizon. Luvisols have high-activity clays throughout the argic horizon and a high base saturation at certain depths.

rdfs:label: phaeozem
IAO:0000115: Phaeozems accommodate soils of relatively wet grassland and forest regions in moderately continental climates. Phaeozems are much like Chernozems and Kastanozems but are leached more intensively. Consequently, they have dark, humus rich surface horizons that, in comparison with Chernozems and Kastanozems, are less rich in bases. Phaeozems may or may not have secondary carbonates but have a high base saturation in the upper metre of the soil.

rdfs:label: solonchak
IAO:0000115: Solonchaks are soils that have a high concentration of soluble salts at some time in the year. Solonchaks are largely confined to the arid and semi-arid climate zones and to coastal regions in all climates.

rdfs:label: vertisol
IAO:0000115: A soil in which there is a high content of expansive clay known as montmorillonite that forms deep cracks in drier seasons or years. Alternate shrinking and swelling causes self-mulching, where the soil material consistently mixes itself, causing vertisols to have an extremely deep A horizon and no B horizon.

rdfs:label: solonetz
IAO:0000115: Solonetz are soils with a dense, strongly structured, clayey subsurface horizon that has a high proportion of adsorbed Na and/or Mg ions. Solonetz that contain free soda (Na2CO3) are strongly alkaline (field pH > 8.5).

rdfs:label: regosol
IAO:0000115: Regosols form a taxonomic remnant group containing all soils that could not be accommodated in any of the other RSGs. In practice, Regosols are very weakly developed mineral soils in unconsolidated materials that do not have a mollic or umbric horizon, are not very shallow or very rich in gravels (Leptosols), sandy (Arenosols) or with fluvic materials (Fluvisols). Regosols are extensive in eroding lands, particularly in arid and semi-arid areas and in mountainous terrain.

rdfs:label: podzol
IAO:0000115: Podzols are soils with a typically ash-grey upper subsurface horizon, bleached by loss of organic matter and iron oxides, on top of a dark accumulation horizon with brown, reddish or black illuviated humus and/or reddish Fe compounds. Podzols occur in humid areas in the boreal and temperate zones and locally also in the tropics.

rdfs:label: fluvisol
IAO:0000115: Fluvisols accommodate genetically young, azonal soils in alluvial deposits.

rdfs:label: enriched soil
IAO:0000115: A portion of enriched soil is a portion of soil with elevated levels of some material entity.

rdfs:label: bagasse
IAO:0000115: The biomass remaining after sugarcane stalks are crushed to extract their juice.

rdfs:label: aerosol
IAO:0000115: Airborne solid particles (also called dust or particulate matter (PM)) or liquid droplets.

rdfs:label: charcoal
IAO:0000115: Charcoal is a light, black residue, consisting of carbon and any remaining ash, obtained by removing water and other volatile constituents from animal and vegetation substances. Charcoal is usually produced by slow pyrolysis, the heating of wood or other substances in the absence of oxygen.

rdfs:label: liquid environmental material
IAO:0000115: An environmental material which is in a liquid state.

rdfs:label: air
IAO:0000115: The mixture of gases (roughly (by molar content/volume: 78% nitrogen, 20.95% oxygen, 0.93% argon, 0.038% carbon dioxide, trace amounts of other gases, and a variable amount (average around 1%) of water vapor) that surrounds the planet Earth.

rdfs:label: water vapour
IAO:0000115: Water vapour is a vapour which is the gas phase of water.

rdfs:label: flame
IAO:0000115: A portion of gas which is emitted by a fire or other exothermic reaction, is of increased temperature, and typically emits light in the visible range.

rdfs:label: water ice
IAO:0000115: Ice is water frozen into a solid state. It can appear transparent or opaque bluish-white color, depending on the presence of impurities or air inclusions. The addition of other materials such as soil may further alter its appearance.

rdfs:label: solid environmental material
IAO:0000115: An environmental material which is in a solid state.

rdfs:label: astrogeological gas
IAO:0000115: An astrogeological volatile which is composed primarily of chemical compounds with boiling points around those of hydrogen and helium.

rdfs:label: pool of specimens
IAO:0000115: A pool of specimens is a mixture of a population of samples which have been gathered from one or more sample populations, obtained by the physical process of mixing individual specimens, e.g.  mixing the DNA collected from the individual fish.

rdfs:label: pregerminated seed
IAO:0000115: Seed soaked in water until the physical process of germination, the penetration of the root though the seed coat, has occurred.

rdfs:label: plant cutting
IAO:0000115: Piece of a plant, often piece of the stem or root, that is used for vegetative propagation.

rdfs:label: ratoon
IAO:0000115: A shoot of a perennial plant.

rdfs:label: whole plant
IAO:0000115: A plant structure (PO:0005679) which is a whole organism.

rdfs:label: seed
IAO:0000115: A multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025496) that develops from a plant ovule (PO:0020003) and has as parts a plant embryo (PO:0009009) enclosed in a seed coat (PO:0009088).

rdfs:label: plant cell
IAO:0000115: A cell which is a plant structure (PO:0009011).

rdfs:label: portion of plant tissue
IAO:0000115: A plant structure (PO:0009011) that consists predominantly of similarly specialized plant cells (PO:0009002) of one or more types.

rdfs:label: embryo plant structure
IAO:0000115: A plant structure (PO:0009011) that is part of an plant embryo (PO:0009009).

rdfs:label: multi-tissue plant structure
