IAO:0000115: A plant structure (PO:0009011) that has as parts two or more portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007) of at least two different types and which through specific morphogenetic processes forms a single structural unit demarcated by primarily bona-fide boundaries from other structural units of different types.

rdfs:label: collective plant structure
IAO:0000115: A plant structure (PO:0009011) that is a proper part of a whole plant (PO:0000003) and includes two or more adjacent plant organs (PO:0009008) or adjacent cardinal organ parts (PO:0025001), along with any associated portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007).

rdfs:label: endolithic environment
IAO:0000115: An endolithic environment is an environment that exists within solid rock.

rdfs:label: anthropogenic environment
IAO:0000115: An anthropogenic environment is an environmental system which is the product of human activity.

rdfs:label: marine environment
IAO:0000115: A marine environment and enviroment which is determined by a marine water body.

rdfs:label: natural environment
IAO:0000115: An environmental system in which minimal to no anthropisation has occurred and non-human agents are the primary determinants of the system's dynamics and composition.

rdfs:label: environmental system determined by a quality
IAO:0000115: An environmental system which is determined by materials bearing roughly homogeneous qualities.

rdfs:label: environmental system determined by a material
IAO:0000115: An environmental system within which an environmental material strongly influences the system's composition and properties.

rdfs:label: environment associated with an animal part or small animal
IAO:0000115: An environmental system determined by part of a living or dead animal, or a whole small animal.

rdfs:label: environment associated with a plant part or small plant
IAO:0000115: An environmental system determined by part of a living or dead plant, or a whole small plant.

rdfs:label: ecosystem
IAO:0000115: An environmental system which includes both living and non-living components.

rdfs:label: anatomical entity environment
IAO:0000115: An environment which is determined by an anatomical entity.

rdfs:label: farmer
IAO:0000115: A person engaged in agriculture, raising living organisms for food or raw materials.

rdfs:label: researcher
IAO:0000115: A person who conducts research.

rdfs:label: student
IAO:0000115: A person that is enrolled or attends classes at a school, college, or university.

rdfs:label: research station employee
IAO:0000115: A person that works in a research station.

rdfs:label: extension agent
IAO:0000115: A person that is employed by the government to assist people in rural areas with methods of farming and home economics.

rdfs:label: faculty member
IAO:0000115: A person that is an educator who works at a college or university.

rdfs:label: data collector
IAO:0000115: A person that has a role of collecting data related to the experiment.

rdfs:label: principal investigator
IAO:0000115: A person that is the holder of an independent grant and the lead researcher for the grant project.

rdfs:label: experiment manager
IAO:0000115: A person that has a role of managing the experiment.

rdfs:label: field laborer
IAO:0000115: A person that has a role of performing the operations required to run the experiment in the field.

rdfs:label: regulator role
IAO:0000115: a regulatory role involved with making and/or enforcing relevant legislation and governmental orders

rdfs:label: material supplier role
IAO:0000115: a role realized through the process of supplying materials such as animal subjects, reagents or other materials used in an investigation.

rdfs:label: slope shape
IAO:0000115: Shape quality that refers to the general shape of a slope in both vertical and horizontal directions.

rdfs:label: elongated
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's length being notably higher than its width.

rdfs:label: sloped
IAO:0000115: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an oblique or slanted direction.

rdfs:label: curvature
IAO:0000115: A surface shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a degree of bending.

rdfs:label: concavity
IAO:0000115: Surface shape that refers to the inward or outward curvature of the surface.

rdfs:label: decreased size
IAO:0000115: A size quality which is relatively low.

rdfs:label: 1-D extent
IAO:0000115: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in one dimension.

rdfs:label: 2-D extent
IAO:0000115: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in two dimensions.

rdfs:label: 3-D extent
IAO:0000115: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in three dimensions.

rdfs:label: structure of soil
IAO:0000115: The structure of some soil.

rdfs:label: composition
IAO:0000115: A single physical entity inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's quantities or relative ratios of subparts.

rdfs:label: permeability
IAO:0000115: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being permeated or pervaded by a gas or liquid (as by osmosis or diffusion).

rdfs:label: wholeness
IAO:0000115: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer includes all its components.

rdfs:label: complexity
IAO:0000115: A monadic quality of continuant inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being intricate and compounded.

rdfs:label: laminar
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's processing the form of a thin plate sheet or layer.

rdfs:label: handedness
IAO:0000115: A behavioral quality inhering ina bearer by virtue of the bearer's unequal distribution of fine motor skill between its left and right hands or feet.

rdfs:label: atmospheric wind intensity
IAO:0000115: The intensity of a atmospheric wind.

rdfs:label: increased quality
IAO:0000115: A quality that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

rdfs:label: decreased quality
IAO:0000115: A quality that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

rdfs:label: number of blocks
IAO:0000115: Number of block used for an experiment.

rdfs:label: number of plots
IAO:0000115: Number of plot used during an experiment.

rdfs:label: number of pots
IAO:0000115: Number of pot used during an experiment.

rdfs:label: number of rows
IAO:0000115: Number of row in a specified area.

rdfs:label: number of treatments
IAO:0000115: Number of treatments tested during an experiment.

rdfs:label: number of replications
IAO:0000115: Number of replications in an experiment.

rdfs:label: number of crops
IAO:0000115: Number of different crop used in an experiment.

rdfs:label: rate
IAO:0000115: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurrence per unit time.

rdfs:label: duration
IAO:0000115: A process quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's magnitude of the temporal extent between the starting and ending point.

rdfs:label: environmental condition
IAO:0000115: An environmental condition is a range of a determinate quality or combination of qualities that are present in an environmental system.

rdfs:label: direction
IAO:0000115: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's orientation in space.

rdfs:label: distance
IAO:0000115: A quality that is the extent of space between two entities.

rdfs:label: sensitivity toward
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to detect or perceive external stimulation.

rdfs:label: position
IAO:0000115: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's spatial location relative to other objects in the vicinity.

rdfs:label: temperature
IAO:0000115: A physical quality of the thermal energy of a system.

rdfs:label: time
IAO:0000115: A quality in which events occur in sequence.

rdfs:label: mass density
IAO:0000115: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence is exerted by the bearer's mass per unit size.

rdfs:label: energy
IAO:0000115: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's capacity to do work.

rdfs:label: pressure
IAO:0000115: A physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's amount of force per unit area it exerts.

rdfs:label: work
IAO:0000115: A physical quality which is equal to the energy transferred by a force to a moving object.

rdfs:label: efficiency
IAO:0000115: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of ratio of the bearer's output to the bearer's input.

rdfs:label: force
IAO:0000115: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's rate of change of momentum.

rdfs:label: electric potential
IAO:0000115: A quality that is equal to the potential energy per unit charge associated with a static (time-invariant) electric field, also called the electrostatic potential.

rdfs:label: proportionality to
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's magnitude in respect to a related entity.

rdfs:label: conductivity
IAO:0000115: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to transmit of an entity through a medium.

rdfs:label: radiation quality
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an bearer by virtue of how that bearer interacts with radiation.

rdfs:label: wetness
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer's being covered by a liquid.

rdfs:label: movement quality
IAO:0000115: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's participation in movement.

rdfs:label: quality of a substance
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its constitution.

rdfs:label: maturity
IAO:0000115: A quality of a single physical entity which is held by a bearer when the latter exhibits complete growth, differentiation, or development.

rdfs:label: shedability
IAO:0000115: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to lose an entitity by natural process.

rdfs:label: concentration of
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the amount of the bearer's there is mixed with another substance.

rdfs:label: substance unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standardised quantity of an element or compound with uniform composition.

rdfs:label: rate unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which represents a standard measurement occurrence of a process per unit time.

rdfs:label: classified data set
IAO:0000115: A data set that is produced as the output of a class prediction data transformation and consists of a data set with assigned class labels.

rdfs:label: clustered data set
IAO:0000115: A data set that is produced as the output of a class discovery data transformation and consists of a data set with assigned discovered class labels.

rdfs:label: curation status specification
IAO:0000115: The curation status of the term. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

rdfs:label: obsolescence reason specification
IAO:0000115: The reason for which a term has been deprecated. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

rdfs:label: denotator type
IAO:0000115: A denotator type indicates how a term should be interpreted from an ontological perspective.

rdfs:label: scalar measurement datum
IAO:0000115: a scalar measurement datum is a measurement datum that is composed of two parts, numerals and a unit label.

rdfs:label: latitude coordinate measurement datum
IAO:0000115: A measurement datum that is the measure of the latitude coordinate of a site.

rdfs:label: longitude coordinate measurement datum
IAO:0000115: A measurement datum that is the measure of the longitude coordinate of a site.

rdfs:label: biological feature identification objective
IAO:0000115: Biological_feature_identification_objective is an objective role carried out by the proposition defining the aim of a study designed to examine or characterize a particular biological feature.

rdfs:label: assay objective
IAO:0000115: an objective specification to determine a specified type of information about an evaluated entity (the material entity bearing evaluant role)

rdfs:label: material transformation objective
IAO:0000115: an objective specifiction that creates an specific output object from input materials.

rdfs:label: specimen collection objective
IAO:0000115: A objective specification to obtain a material entity for potential use as an input during an investigation.

rdfs:label: training objective
IAO:0000115: An objective specification which is fulfilled by the provision of some training.

rdfs:label: selective organism creation objective
IAO:0000115: an objective specification to generate a population or type of organism within species that have some uniform behavioral, morphological, physiological, or genetic characteristics with similarly bred organisms.

rdfs:label: data transformation objective
IAO:0000115: An objective specification to transformation input data into output data

rdfs:label: application method
IAO:0000115: A plan specification which describes how a material entity is applied to another material entity.

rdfs:label: irrigation method
IAO:0000115: A plan specification which describes how water is applied to plants or soil.

rdfs:label: planting distribution
IAO:0000115: Pattern used to plant crop in field.

rdfs:label: software
IAO:0000115:
Software is a plan specification composed of a series of instructions that can be 
interpreted by or directly executed by a processing unit.

rdfs:label: algorithm
IAO:0000115: A plan specification which describes the inputs and output of mathematical functions as well as workflow of execution for achieving an predefined objective. Algorithms are realized usually by means of implementation as computer programs for execution by automata.

rdfs:label: protocol
IAO:0000115: A plan specification which has sufficient level of detail and quantitative information to communicate it between investigation agents, so that different investigation agents will reliably be able to independently reproduce the process.

rdfs:label: study design
IAO:0000115: A plan specification comprised of protocols (which may specify how and what kinds of data will be gathered) that are executed as part of an investigation and is realized during a study design execution.

rdfs:label: graph
IAO:0000115: A diagram that presents one or more tuples of information by mapping those tuples in to a two dimensional space in a non arbitrary way.

rdfs:label: histologic grade according to AJCC 7th edition
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a histologic grade assigned to a tumor slide specimen according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) 7th Edition grading system.

rdfs:label: histologic grade according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a histologic grade assigned to a tumor slide specimen according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System.

rdfs:label: histologic grade for ovarian tumor
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a histologic grade assigned to a ovarian tumor.

rdfs:label: pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of colorectal cancer following the rules of the TNM American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) version 7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

rdfs:label: pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer following the rules of the TNM American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) version 7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

rdfs:label: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

rdfs:label: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

rdfs:label: pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of colorectal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

rdfs:label: pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

rdfs:label: pathologic lymph node stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

rdfs:label: pathologic lymph node stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

rdfs:label: pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of colon cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

rdfs:label: pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

rdfs:label: pathologic distant metastases stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

rdfs:label: pathologic distant metastases stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a  pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

rdfs:label: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of the stage of a cancer according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) v7 staging systems.

rdfs:label: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of the stage of a gynecologic cancer according to the International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics (FIGO) staging systems.

rdfs:label: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the FIGO classification system.

rdfs:label: performance status value specification
IAO:0000115: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of a participant's performance status (general well-being and activities of daily life).

rdfs:label: manufacturing process
IAO:0000115: A planned process during which raw or recycled materials are transformed into products for use or sale using labour and machines, tools, chemical and biological processing, or formulation.

rdfs:label: construction process
IAO:0000115: An process during which natural or manufactured materials and products are processed and arranged by humans or their technology into structures.

rdfs:label: explosive eruption
IAO:0000115: An explosive eruption is a volcanic process in which pressurised magma is violently expelled and froths into volcanic ash. Explosive eruptions can eject a cloud of rocks, dust, gas, and pyroclastic material  which may then collapse, creating a pyroclastic flow of hot volcanic matter.

rdfs:label: hydrological precipitation process
IAO:0000115: Hydrological precipitation is a process during which any product of the condensation of atmospheric water vapour is pulled to the planetary surface by gravity.

rdfs:label: soil erosion
IAO:0000115: Soil erosion is a process in which exogenic processes remove soil from one location on the Earth's crust and transport it to another location where it is deposited.

rdfs:label: combustion process
IAO:0000115: Combustion or burning is a high-temperature exothermic redox chemical reaction between a fuel and an oxidant that produces oxidized, often gaseous products, in a mixture termed as smoke.

rdfs:label: no-till
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which the soil is left undisturbed apart from where the seeds or planting material are placed.

rdfs:label: drip irrigation process
IAO:0000115: A localized irrigation process in which water is conveyed under pressure through a pipe system where it drips slowly onto the soil close to the plants.

rdfs:label: pitcher irrigation process
IAO:0000115: A localized irrigation process in which water is distributed by diffusion and capillary action through the wall of buried unglazed clay pot.

rdfs:label: subsurface drip irrigation process
IAO:0000115: A localized irrigation process in which water is conveyed under pressure through a buried pipe system where it drips slowly below the soil surface close to plants' roots.

rdfs:label: center-pivot irrigation process
IAO:0000115: A sprinkler irrigation process in which water is dispersed through a long, segmented arm that revolves around a pivot point and covers a circular area.

rdfs:label: bassin irrigation process
IAO:0000115: A surface irrigation process in which water is applied into basins. Basins are flat areas of land surronded by low bunds.

rdfs:label: border irrigation process
IAO:0000115: A surface irrigation process in which water is distributed to an area divided into borders. Borders are long, sloping strips of land separated by bunds. Water is applied to the top end of borders.

rdfs:label: furrow irrigation process
IAO:0000115: A surface irrigation process in which water is carried into small channels called furrows down the land slope between the plant rows. Water is applied to the top end of each furrow and infiltrates into the soil as it moves along the slope channel.

rdfs:label: uncontrolled flooding process
IAO:0000115: A surface irrigation process in which water is spread over a flat area without control over water flow or prior preparation.

rdfs:label: mechanical pest destruction process
IAO:0000115: A mechanical pest control process in which pests are killed.

rdfs:label: mechanical pest exclusion process
IAO:0000115: A mechanical pest control process in which pests are kept away.

rdfs:label: organisms importation process
IAO:0000115: A biological pest control process in which organisms that will help to manage pests are introduced to a new locale where they do not occur naturally.

rdfs:label: organisms augmentation process
IAO:0000115: A biological pest control process in which organisms that help to manage pests are released to boost the naturally occurring population.

rdfs:label: organisms conservation process
IAO:0000115: A biological pest control process in which suitable habitat or food are provided to the naturally occurring population of organisms that help to manage pests.

rdfs:label: intensive rotational grazing
IAO:0000115: A rotational grazing management system that implies many paddocks are utilized and livestock are moved on a frequent basis. It provides more stable production during poor growing conditions, greater yield, higher quality, decreased weed and erosion, and uniform soil fertility levels.

rdfs:label: creep grazing
IAO:0000115: A grazzing management system that allows young farm animals to graze part of the pasture before the adults. It employs a gate through which young animals, but not adults, can pass to get first choice of fresh feed in the next door paddock.

rdfs:label: first-last grazing
IAO:0000115: A gazing management system in which two or more groups of animal, usually with different nutritional needs, graze the same paddock but at different time.

rdfs:label: adding a material entity into a target
IAO:0000115: is a process with the objective to place a material entity bearing the 'material to be added role' into a material bearing the 'target of material addition role'.

rdfs:label: support vector machine
IAO:0000115: A support vector machine is a data transformation with a class prediction objective based on the construction of a separating hyperplane that maximizes the margin between two data sets of vectors in n-dimensional space.

rdfs:label: CART
IAO:0000115: A CART (classification and regression trees) is a data transformation method for producing a classification or regression model with a tree-based structure.

rdfs:label: k-nearest neighbors
IAO:0000115: A k-nearest neighbors is a data transformation which achieves a class discovery or partitioning objective, in which an input data object with vector y is assigned to a class label based upon the k closest training data set points to y; where k is the largest value that class label is assigned.

rdfs:label: statistical model validation
IAO:0000115: A data transformation which assesses how the results of a statistical analysis will generalize to an independent data set.

rdfs:label: k-means clustering
IAO:0000115: A k-means clustering is a data transformation which achieves a class discovery or partitioning objective, which takes as input a collection of objects (represented as points in multidimensional space) and which partitions them into a specified number k of clusters. The algorithm attempts to find the centers of natural clusters in the data. The most common form of the algorithm starts by partitioning the input points into k initial sets, either at random or using some heuristic data. It then calculates the mean point, or centroid, of each set. It constructs a new partition by associating each point with the closest centroid. Then the centroids are recalculated for the new clusters, and the algorithm repeated by alternate applications of these two steps until convergence, which is obtained when the points no longer switch clusters (or alternatively centroids are no longer changed).

rdfs:label: hierarchical clustering
IAO:0000115: A hierarchical clustering is a data transformation which achieves a class discovery objective, which takes as input data item and builds a hierarchy of clusters. The traditional representation of this hierarchy is a tree (visualized by a dendrogram), with the individual input objects at one end (leaves) and a single cluster containing every object at the other (root).

rdfs:label: dimensionality reduction
IAO:0000115: A dimensionality reduction is data partitioning which transforms each input m-dimensional vector (x_1, x_2, ..., x_m) into an output n-dimensional vector (y_1, y_2, ..., y_n), where n is smaller than m.

rdfs:label: EC 3.5.1.* (non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase) inhibitor
IAO:0000115: An EC 3.5.* (hydrolases acting on non-peptide C-N bonds) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase (EC 3.5.1.*).

rdfs:label: mammalian metabolite
IAO:0000115: Any animal metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in mammals.

rdfs:label: crustacean metabolite
IAO:0000115: An animal metabolite produced by arthropods such as crabs, lobsters, crayfish, shrimps and krill.

rdfs:label: Saccharomyces cerevisiae metabolite
IAO:0000115: Any  fungal metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in Baker's yeast (Saccharomyces cerevisiae).

rdfs:label: Escherichia coli metabolite
IAO:0000115: Any bacterial metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in Escherichia coli.

rdfs:label: meter
IAO:0000115: A length unit which is equal to the length of the path traveled by light in vacuum during a time interval of 1/299 792 458 of a second.

rdfs:label: centimeter
IAO:0000115: A length unit which is equal to one hundredth of a meter or 10^[-2] m.

rdfs:label: millimeter
IAO:0000115: A length unit which is equal to one thousandth of a meter or 10^[-3] m.

rdfs:label: kilogram
IAO:0000115: A mass unit which is equal to the mass of the International Prototype Kilogram kept by the BIPM at Svres, France.

rdfs:label: gram
IAO:0000115: A mass unit which is equal to one thousandth of a kilogram or 10^[-3] kg.

rdfs:label: milligram
IAO:0000115: A mass unit which is equal to one thousandth of a gram or 10^[-3] g.

rdfs:label: second
IAO:0000115: A time unit which is equal to the duration of 9 192 631 770 periods of the radiation corresponding to the transition between the two hyperfine levels of the ground state of the caesium 133 atom.

rdfs:label: minute
IAO:0000115: A time unit which is equal to 60 seconds.

rdfs:label: hour
IAO:0000115: A time unit which is equal to 3600 seconds or 60 minutes.

rdfs:label: day
IAO:0000115: A time unit which is equal to 24 hours.

rdfs:label: week
IAO:0000115: A time unit which is equal to 7 days.

rdfs:label: month
IAO:0000115: A time unit which is approximately equal to the length of time of one of cycle of the moon's phases which in science is taken to be equal to 30 days.

rdfs:label: year
IAO:0000115: A time unit which is equal to 12 months which in science is taken to be equal to 365.25 days.

rdfs:label: degree Celsius
IAO:0000115: A temperature unit which is equal to one kelvin degree. However, they have their zeros at different points. The centigrade scale has its zero at 273.15 K.

rdfs:label: degree Fahrenheit
IAO:0000115: A temperature unit which is equal to 5/9ths of a kelvin. Negative 40 degrees Fahrenheit is equal to negative 40 degrees Celsius.

rdfs:label: mass percentage
IAO:0000115: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the mass of a substance in a mixture as a percentage of the mass of the entire mixture.

rdfs:label: pH
IAO:0000115: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the acidity of a solution in terms of activity of hydrogen ions (H+).

rdfs:label: specific volume unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the volume of a given mass of substance (the reciprocal of density).

rdfs:label: milliliter
IAO:0000115: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of a liter or 10^[-3] L, or to 1 cubic centimeter.

rdfs:label: liter
IAO:0000115: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of a cubic meter or 10^[-3] m^[3], or to 1 decimeter.

rdfs:label: rotational frequency unit
IAO:0000115: A unit which is a standard measure of the number of rotations in a given time.

rdfs:label: microliters per minute
IAO:0000115: A volumetric flow rate unit which is equal to one microliter volume through a given surface in one minute.

rdfs:label: aeroform
IAO:0000115: An aeroform is a geographic feature which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of gaseous or aerosolised material held in shape by one or more environmental processes.

rdfs:label: nucleon
IAO:0000115: Heavy nuclear particle: proton or neutron.

rdfs:label: decreased position
IAO:0000115: A positional which is relatively low.

rdfs:label: increased temperature
IAO:0000115: A temperature which is relatively high.

rdfs:label: increased position
IAO:0000115: A position which is relatively high.

rdfs:label: tillage process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which soil is mechanicaly mixed, stirred or overturned.

rdfs:label: mowing process
IAO:0000115: A cutting process in which the above ground of the plants are cut or shred. It can be used to reduce weed seed populations or restrict the growth of weeds.

rdfs:label: single-axle tractor
IAO:0000115: Atractorwith oneaxle, self-powered and self-propelled. The operator usually walks behind it or rides the implement being towed.

rdfs:label: two-axle tractor
IAO:0000115: A tractor with two axles. Agricultural implements may be towed behind or mounted on the tractor, and the tractor may also provide a source of power if the implement is mechanized.

rdfs:label: levelling board
IAO:0000115: Board used in field with a total water coverage to shape field surface. Weight can be added to the board.

rdfs:label: levelling bucket
IAO:0000115: Bucket dragged by animal or tractor to shape soil surface. Bucket dimensions and capacity vary according to the available power source and field conditions.

rdfs:label: laser-controlled bucket
IAO:0000115: A bucket tracted by a tractor and controlled by a laser to shape soil surface. A laser transmitter transmits a laser beam, which is intercepted by the laser receiver mounted on the leveling bucket. The control panel mounted on the tractor interprets the signal from the receiver and raises or lowers the bucket.

rdfs:label: chain harrow
IAO:0000115: An implement consisting of a heavy framework having high numbers of steel tines on an harrow mat.

rdfs:label: tine harrow
IAO:0000115: An implement consisting of a heavy framework having several spikes or tines, and dragged by an animal or a tractor.

rdfs:label: tillage implement
IAO:0000115: An implement that is used during a tillage process.

rdfs:label: manure spreader
IAO:0000115: An implement used to distribute manure over a field. It usually consists of a trailer towed behind a tractor with a rotating mechanism driven by the tractor's power take off.

rdfs:label: slurry injector
IAO:0000115: An implement designed to inject slurry into the soil.

rdfs:label: broadcast spreader
IAO:0000115: An implement that consists of a hopper, a metering unit, and a distribution device that uses centrifugal force to spread material like seeds, fertilizer granules, liming material, onto the soil surface.

rdfs:label: backpack sprayer
IAO:0000115: An implement that is used to spray liquid and that is fitted with a harness on the operator back.

rdfs:label: hand sprayer
IAO:0000115: An implement that is used to spray liquid and is help in the hand. It usually has an air pump which compresses air into the tanks and pressurizes the liquid to spray.

rdfs:label: airblast sprayer
IAO:0000115:
An implement that uses a combination of air and liquid to deliver liquid material to the target.
It includes include nozzles that deliver spray droplets directly into a high-speed airstream. The air blast shatters the drops of lidquid material into fine droplets and transports them to the target.

rdfs:label: furrow opener
IAO:0000115: An implement which is used to create well-defined grooves in the soil where some material like seeds or fertilizer can be placed at a proper depth.

rdfs:label: sowing implement
IAO:0000115: An implement that is used during a sowing process.

rdfs:label: tyne opener planter
IAO:0000115: A curved metal bar used to open the soil before putting the seed into the soil.

rdfs:label: dibbling stick
IAO:0000115: Manually operated device for creating a conical cavity in the soil for sowing of seeds. It consists of a wooden round stick with one end having a sheet metal cone. The other end is provided with a handgrip.

rdfs:label: naveen dibbler
IAO:0000115: Manually operated hand tool which consists of a seed hopper, cell roller for metering of seeds, spring actuated jaws for penetration in the soil, pipe and handle.

rdfs:label: hand dibbler
IAO:0000115: An tool made of mild steel flat or leaf spring by forging operation. The working end is flattened and edge made sharp for easy penetration in the soil.

rdfs:label: rotary dibbler
IAO:0000115: Manually operated push device for dibbling of medium and bold size seeds. It consists of a rotating dibbling head with penetrating jaws, covering-cum-transport wheel, seed hopper with cell wooden roller and a handle.

rdfs:label: earth auger
IAO:0000115: Manually operated hand tool that consists of cutter head having semicircular blades connected to pipe with the help of clamp and flange. The connecting pipe is further connected to a handle.

rdfs:label: single disc opener planter
IAO:0000115: A flat and circular piece of metal used to open the soil before putting the seed into the soil.

rdfs:label: double disck opener planter
IAO:0000115: Double flat and circular piece of metal used to open the soil before putting the seed into the soil.

rdfs:label: sickle
IAO:0000115: Agricultural tool that is hand-held and composed of a curved blade with a sharp inside and a handle. It is used for harvesting, or reaping, grain crops or cutting succulent forage chiefly for feeding livestock, either freshly cut or dried as hay.

rdfs:label: flail
IAO:0000115: Agricultural tool made from two or more large sticks attached by a short chain; one stick is held and swung, causing the other to strike a pile of grain, loosening the husks.

rdfs:label: scythe
IAO:0000115: Agricultural tool that consists of a shaft about 170 centimetres (67 in) long made of wood or metal. The shaft has either one or two short handles at right angles to it, usually one near the upper end and always another roughly in the middle. A curved, steel blade between 60 to 90 centimetres (24 to 35 in) long is mounted at the lower end at 90, or less, to the shaft. It is hand powered.

rdfs:label: irrigation tube
IAO:0000115: Object with a tube shape used to carry irrigation water through the field

rdfs:label: center pivot irrigation machine
IAO:0000115: Form of overhead sprinkler irrigation consisting of several segments of pipe joined together and supported by trusses, mounted on wheeled towers with sprinklers positioned along its length. The machine moves in a circular pattern and is fed with water from the pivot point at the center of the circle.

rdfs:label: (13)C-modified compound
IAO:0000115: An isotopically modified compound in which the abundance of a (13)C isotope at one or more positions has been increased above that of the naturally occurring level.

rdfs:label: inorganic phosphate
IAO:0000115: Any  phosphate that contains no carbon atom.

rdfs:label: ammonium nitrate
IAO:0000115: The ammonium salt of nitric acid.

rdfs:label: anion
IAO:0000115: A monoatomic or polyatomic species having one or more elementary charges of the electron.

rdfs:label: polyatomic ion
IAO:0000115: An ion consisting of more than one atom.

rdfs:label: cation
IAO:0000115: A monoatomic or polyatomic species having one or more elementary charges of the proton.

rdfs:label: monoatomic entity
IAO:0000115: A monoatomic entity is a molecular entity consisting of a single atom.

rdfs:label: gas molecular entity
IAO:0000115: Any main group molecular entity that is gaseous at standard temperature and pressure (STP; 0degreeC and 100 kPa).

rdfs:label: s-block molecular entity
IAO:0000115: An s-block molecular entity is a molecular entity containing one or more atoms of an s-block element.

rdfs:label: p-block molecular entity
IAO:0000115: A main group molecular entity that contains one or more atoms of a p-block element.

rdfs:label: molecule
IAO:0000115: Any polyatomic entity that is an electrically neutral entity consisting of more than one atom.

rdfs:label: heteroatomic molecular entity
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity consisting of two or more chemical elements.

rdfs:label: acyl group
IAO:0000115: An organic group formed by removing one or more hydroxy groups from an oxoacid that has the general structure RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0). Although the term is almost always applied to organic compounds, with carboxylic acid as the oxoacid, acyl groups can in principle be derived from other types of acids such as sulfonic acids or phosphonic acids.

rdfs:label: p-block element atom
IAO:0000115: Any main group element atom belonging to the p-block of the periodic table.

rdfs:label: transition element atom
IAO:0000115: An element whose atom has an incomplete d sub-shell, or which can give rise to cations with an incomplete d sub-shell.

rdfs:label: urea ammonium nitrate
IAO:0000115: A mixture consisting of urea (typically 40-45%), ammonium nitrate (30-35%) and water (30-20%). It is used as a nitrogen fertilizer in agriculture.

rdfs:label: calcium ammonium nitrate
IAO:0000115: A mixture obtained by combining ammonium nitrate, calcium nitrate and water. It is widely used as a nitrogen fertilizer in agriculture.

rdfs:label: electron
IAO:0000115: Elementary particle not affected by the strong force having a spin 1/2, a negative elementary charge and a rest mass of 0.000548579903(13) u, or 0.51099906(15) MeV.

rdfs:label: fallow land
IAO:0000115: An agricultural field that is set aside for a period of time before it is cultivated again; or an agricultral field that is under permanent crops, meadows or pastures and that is not being used for such purposes for a period of at least one year.

rdfs:label: paddy field
IAO:0000115: A flooded parcel of arable land used for growing rice and other semiaquatic crops.

rdfs:label: wetland
IAO:0000115: An area that is inundated or saturated by surface or ground water at a frequency and duration sufficient to support, and that under normal circumstances do support, a prevalence of vegetation typically adapted for life in saturated soil conditions.

rdfs:label: grassland
IAO:0000115: An area in which grasses (Graminae) are a significant component of the vegetation.

rdfs:label: woodland
IAO:0000115: Land having a cover of trees, shrubs, or both.

rdfs:label: tundra
IAO:0000115: Treeless, level, or gently rolling plains characteristic of arctic or subarctic regions, having a permanently frozen subsoil, and usually supporting low growing vegetation such as lichens, mosses, and stunted shrubs.

rdfs:label: oasis
IAO:0000115: An oasis is a vegetated area located in a desert, supplied with water from a water source which it surrounds, and surrounded by arid soil, sand, or rock.

rdfs:label: plant feed
IAO:0000115: Plant feed is a biotic mesoscopic physical object consisting of any foodstuff that is used specifically to feed plants.

rdfs:label: piece of rock
IAO:0000115: An abiotic  mesoscopic feature made of the mineral material of the crust of the Earth.

rdfs:label: farmer field
IAO:0000115: Experimental site in which the experiment is implemented on the field of a farmer.

rdfs:label: research station field
IAO:0000115: Experimental site in which the experiment is done in a the field of a research station.

rdfs:label: greenhouse
IAO:0000115: An experimental site in which the experiment is performed in a structure with walls and roof made chiefly of transparent material, such as glass, with the possibility to regulate climatic conditions.

rdfs:label: governmental forest
IAO:0000115: Experimental site where the experiment is done in a forest owned by a government.

rdfs:label: private forest
IAO:0000115: Experimental site where the experiment is done in a private forest.

rdfs:label: planet
IAO:0000115: A planet is an astronomical body orbiting a star or stellar remnant that is massive enough to be rounded by its own gravity, is not massive enough to cause thermonuclear fusion, and has cleared its neighbouring region of planetesimals.

rdfs:label: meteoroid
IAO:0000115: An astronomical body which is composed of rocky or metallic materials and is considerably smaller than asteroids.

rdfs:label: anthropogenic geographic feature
IAO:0000115:
An anthropogenic geographic feature is a geographic feature
resulting from the influence of human beings on nature.

rdfs:label: hydrographic feature
IAO:0000115: A geographical feature associated with water.

rdfs:label: water body
IAO:0000115: An accumulation of water of varying size.

rdfs:label: island
IAO:0000115: Area of dry or relatively dry land surrounded by water or low wetland.

rdfs:label: layer
IAO:0000115: A layer is a quantity of some material which has comparable thickness and usually covers some surface.

rdfs:label: coast
IAO:0000115: A coast is the area where land meets the sea, ocean, or lake.

rdfs:label: hydroform
IAO:0000115: A hydroform is a geographic feature which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of liquid water held in shape by an environmental process.

rdfs:label: cryoform
IAO:0000115: A geographic feature which is primarily composed of a continuous mass of snow and/or ice.

rdfs:label: oceanic island
IAO:0000115: An island that does not sit on a continental shelf, and is of volcanic origin.

rdfs:label: volcano
IAO:0000115: An opening, or rupture, in the Earth's surface or crust, which allows hot, molten rock, ash and gases to escape from deep below the surface.

rdfs:label: chalk
IAO:0000115: A soft, white, porous limestone.

rdfs:label: bagasse
IAO:0000115: The biomass remaining after sugarcane stalks are crushed to extract their juice.

rdfs:label: compost
IAO:0000115: The aerobically decomposed remnants of organic materials.

rdfs:label: hay
IAO:0000115: Hay is grass, legumes or other herbaceous plants that have been cut, dried, and stored for use as animal fodder, particularly for grazing livestock such as cattle, horses, goats, and sheep.

rdfs:label: silage
IAO:0000115: A fermented, high-moisture forage that can be fed to ruminants.

rdfs:label: straw
IAO:0000115: An agricultural byproduct, the dry stalk of a cereal plant, after the nutrient grain or seed has been removed.

rdfs:label: liquid aerosol
IAO:0000115: An aerosol which is primarily composed of liquid droplets.

rdfs:label: solid aerosol
IAO:0000115: An aerosol which is primarily composed of solid particles.

rdfs:label: water
IAO:0000115: An environmental material primarily composed of dihydrogen oxide in its liquid form.

rdfs:label: atmospheric water vapour
IAO:0000115: Atmospheric water vapour is water vapour that is part of an atmosphere.

rdfs:label: hydrocarbon flame
IAO:0000115: A flame which is produced by the combustion of hydrocarbon fuel.

rdfs:label: rock
IAO:0000115: A rock is a naturally occurring solid aggregate of one or more minerals or mineraloids.

rdfs:label: mineral material
IAO:0000115: A mineral material is an environmental material which is primarily composed of some substance that is naturally occurring, solid and stable at room temperature, representable by a chemical formula, usually abiogenic, and that has an ordered atomic structure.

rdfs:label: plant embryo
IAO:0000115: A whole plant (PO:0000003) that participates in the plant embryo stage (PO:0007631).

rdfs:label: native plant cell
IAO:0000115: A plant cell (PO:0009002) that is either part of a multicellular whole plant (PO:0000003) 'in vivo' or a unicellular organism 'in natura' (i.e. part of a natural environment).

rdfs:label: portion of meristem tissue
IAO:0000115: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) in which plant cells (PO:0009002) have retained their embryonic characteristics, or have reverted to them secondarily, and that divide to produce new cells that can undergo differentiation to form mature tissues, i.e. they have a capacity for morphogenesis and growth.

rdfs:label: portion of embryo plant tissue
IAO:0000115: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).

rdfs:label: embryo plant cell
IAO:0000115: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).

rdfs:label: fruit
IAO:0000115: A multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025496) that develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062), or a single carpel (PO:0009030), and at maturity may have as parts one or more seeds (PO:0009010).

rdfs:label: plant organ
IAO:0000115: A multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025496) that is a functional unit, is a proper part of a whole plant (PO:0000003), and includes portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007) of at least two different types that derive from a common developmental path.

rdfs:label: collective plant organ structure
IAO:0000115: A collective plant structure (PO:0025497) that is a proper part of a whole plant (PO:0000003), and is composed of two or more adjacent plant organs (PO:0009008) and the associated portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007).

rdfs:label: high temperature environment
IAO:0000115: A high temperature environment is an environment in which material entities are exposed to increased levels of heat radiation or which have molecules or atoms moving randomly with increased levels of average kinietic energy.

rdfs:label: high osmolarity environment
IAO:0000115: A high osmolarity environment is an environment in which entities are exposed to high concentrations of solutes.

rdfs:label: aquatic environment
IAO:0000115: An environment whose dynamics are strongly influenced by water.

rdfs:label: soil environment
IAO:0000115: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by soil.

rdfs:label: aerosol environment
IAO:0000115: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by an aerosol.

rdfs:label: biome
IAO:0000115: A biome is an environmental system to which resident ecological communities have evolved adaptations.

rdfs:label: environmental system determined by an organism
IAO:0000115: An environmental system which is determined by a living organism.

rdfs:label: terraced
IAO:0000115: Slope on which terraces have been build.

rdfs:label: irregular shape
IAO:0000115: Slope shape irregular.

rdfs:label: convex
IAO:0000115: A shape quality that obtains by virtue of the bearer having inward facing edges; having a surface or boundary that curves or bulges outward, as the exterior of a sphere.

rdfs:label: concave
IAO:0000115: A shape quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's curving inward.

rdfs:label: straight
IAO:0000115: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being free of curves, bends, or angles.

rdfs:label: flattened
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's surface becoming more extended in a plane.

rdfs:label: height
IAO:0000115: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's vertical dimension of extension.

rdfs:label: length
IAO:0000115: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points.

rdfs:label: thickness
IAO:0000115: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the dimension through an object as opposed to its length or width.

rdfs:label: width
IAO:0000115: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance from one side of an object to another side which is opposite.

rdfs:label: depth
IAO:0000115: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's downward or backward or inward dimenision.

rdfs:label: area
IAO:0000115: A 2-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's two dimensional extent.

rdfs:label: volume
IAO:0000115: A 3-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's amount of 3-dimensional space it occupies.

rdfs:label: porosity of soil
IAO:0000115: The porosity of some soil.

rdfs:label: composition of soil
IAO:0000115: The composition of some soil.

rdfs:label: granular
IAO:0000115: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing granules.

rdfs:label: porosity
IAO:0000115: A permeability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to admit the passage of gas or liquid through pores or interstices.

rdfs:label: broken
IAO:0000115: A broken quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being broken open.

rdfs:label: complex
IAO:0000115: A complexity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being intricate and compounded.

rdfs:label: left handedness
IAO:0000115: Handedness where the organism preferentially uses the left hand or foot for tasks requiring the use of a single hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

rdfs:label: right handedness
IAO:0000115: Handedness where the organism preferentially uses the right hand or foot for tasks requiring the use of a single hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

rdfs:label: ambidextrous handedness
IAO:0000115: Handedness where the organism exhibits no overall dominance in the use of right or left hand or foot in the performance of tasks that require one hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

rdfs:label: number of crops previously cultivated
IAO:0000115: Number of crops cultivated at the same time during the previous year in the field where the experiment is done.

rdfs:label: frequency
IAO:0000115: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of the number of the bearer's repetitive actions in a particular time.

rdfs:label: tropical
IAO:0000115: A tropical condition is an environmental condition in which an environmental system receives high yearly solar irradiance per unit area and, on Earth, the Sun reaches a subsolar point at least once during the solar year. This results in a hot and moist year-round climate at low elevations, which have a monthly average temperature above 18 degrees Celsius.

rdfs:label: arid
IAO:0000115: An environmental condition in which annual precipitation is less than half of annual potential evapotranspiration.

rdfs:label: plot spacing
IAO:0000115: Distance quality that represents the distance between two plots.

rdfs:label: row spacing
IAO:0000115: Distance between two rows.

rdfs:label: hill spacing
IAO:0000115: Distance between two hills.

rdfs:label: plant spacing in a row
IAO:0000115: Average distance between plants in a same row.

rdfs:label: threshold
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's sensitivity towards a fixed location or value where a change is observed; upper limit.

rdfs:label: spatial pattern
IAO:0000115: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting repetition of placement of its parts.

rdfs:label: orientation
IAO:0000115: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's placement which is defined by the angle between the bearer and an axis, or the angle between the bearer and another object.

rdfs:label: elevation
IAO:0000115: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's vertical distance of a point above or below a reference surface.

rdfs:label: temperature of environmental material
IAO:0000115: The temperature of some environmental material.

rdfs:label: frozen
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being kept below its freezing point.

rdfs:label: mass density of soil
IAO:0000115: The mass density of some soil.

rdfs:label: area density
IAO:0000115: A density quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence exerted by the bearer's mass on a given area.

rdfs:label: linear density
IAO:0000115: A density quality which is equal to the mass exerting an influence on a one-dimensional object.

rdfs:label: volumetric density
IAO:0000115: A density quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence exerted by the bearer's mass on a given volume.

rdfs:label: weight
IAO:0000115: A physical quality inhering in a bearer that has mass near a gravitational body.

rdfs:label: percent of experiment area damaged
IAO:0000115: Percentage of the area of the experiment damaged due to a complication during the experiment.

rdfs:label: nitrogen recovery efficiency
IAO:0000115: Amount of nutrient in the crop as a ratio of the amount applied or available.

rdfs:label: nitrogen use efficiency
IAO:0000115: Ratio between the amount of nitrogen fertilizer removed from the field by the crop and the amount of nitrogen fertilizer applied. It provides information about the relative utilization of additional nitrogen applied to a agricultural production system.

rdfs:label: organic fertilizer carbon to nitrogen ratio
IAO:0000115: Carbon-to-nitrogen ratio is a ratio of the mass of carbon to the mass of nitrogen in an organic fertilizer.

rdfs:label: electrical conductivity
IAO:0000115: A conductivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to convey electricity.

rdfs:label: electromagnetic (EM) radiation quality
IAO:0000115: A physical quality that inheres in an bearer by virtue of how that bearer interacts with electromagnetic radiation.

rdfs:label: wetness of soil
IAO:0000115: The wetness of some soil.

rdfs:label: wet
IAO:0000115: A wetness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being covered by a liquid.

rdfs:label: dry
IAO:0000115: A wetness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's not being covered by a liquid.

rdfs:label: speed
IAO:0000115: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's scalar absolute value of the rate of change of the bearer's position.

rdfs:label: flow rate
IAO:0000115: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's motion characteristic.

rdfs:label: quality of a solid
IAO:0000115: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity characterized by particles arranged such that their shape and volume are relatively stable.

rdfs:label: quality of a gas
IAO:0000115: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity consisting of particles that have neither a defined volume nor defined shape.

rdfs:label: quality of a liquid
IAO:0000115: A physical quality inhering in an entity exhibiting the physical characteristics of an amorphous (non-crystalline) form of matter between a gas and a solid that has a definite volume, but no definite shape.

rdfs:label: mature
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting complete growth, differentiation, or development.

rdfs:label: semi-deciduous(plant)
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a plant by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being between evergeen and deciduous.

rdfs:label: concentration of ammonium in soil
IAO:0000115: The concentration of a ammonium when measured in soil.

rdfs:label: concentration of nitrate in soil
IAO:0000115: The concentration of a nitrate when measured in soil.

rdfs:label: osmolarity
IAO:0000115: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's amount of osmoles of solute per liter of solution.

rdfs:label: acidity
IAO:0000115: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing acid (hydrogen ions).

rdfs:label: length measurement datum
IAO:0000115: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measurement of length quality

rdfs:label: mass measurement datum
IAO:0000115: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measurement of mass quality

rdfs:label: time measurement datum
IAO:0000115: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measuring a temporal interval

rdfs:label: rate measurement datum
IAO:0000115: A scalar measurement datum that represents the number of events occuring over a time interval

rdfs:label: organism feature identification objective
IAO:0000115: Organism_feature_identification_objective is a biological_feature_identification_objective role describing a study designed to examine or characterize a biological feature monitored at the level of the organism, e.g. height, weight, stage of development, stage of life cycle.

rdfs:label: manufacturing objective
IAO:0000115: is the objective to manufacture a material of a certain function (device)

rdfs:label: material combination objective
IAO:0000115: is an objective to obtain an output material that contains several input materials.

rdfs:label: genetic transformation objective
IAO:0000115: a material transformation objective aims to create genetically modified organism or cell

rdfs:label: averaging objective
IAO:0000115: An averaging objective is a data transformation objective where the aim is to perform mean calculations on the input of the data transformation.

rdfs:label: decision tree induction objective
IAO:0000115: A decision tree induction objective is a data transformation objective in which a tree-like graph of edges and nodes is created and from which the selection of each branch requires that some type of logical decision is made.

rdfs:label: partitioning objective
IAO:0000115: A partitioning objective is a data transformation objective where the aim is to generate a collection of disjoint non-empty subsets whose union equals a non-empty input set.

rdfs:label: center calculation objective
IAO:0000115: A center calculation objective is a data transformation objective where the aim is to calculate the center of an input data set.

rdfs:label: class discovery objective
IAO:0000115: A class discovery objective (sometimes called unsupervised classification) is a data transformation objective where the aim is to organize input data  (typically vectors of attributes) into classes, where the number of classes and their specifications are not known a priori. Depending on usage, the class assignment can be definite or probabilistic.

rdfs:label: class prediction objective
IAO:0000115:
A class prediction objective (sometimes called supervised classification) is a data transformation objective where the aim is to create a predictor from training data through a machine learning technique. The training data consist of pairs of objects (typically vectors of attributes) and
class labels for these objects. The resulting predictor can be used to attach class labels to any valid novel input object. Depending on usage, the prediction can be definite or probabilistic. A classification is learned from the training data and can then be tested on test data.

rdfs:label: aerial application
IAO:0000115: An application method in which a liquid material entity is applied by aircraft to an area.

rdfs:label: band application
IAO:0000115: An application method in which a material entity is applied in bands below, above, on one side, or on both sides of seeds or seedlings at planting.

rdfs:label: broadcast application method
IAO:0000115: An application method which specifies how a material entity is to be uniformly applied to an area.

rdfs:label: chemical basal application
IAO:0000115: An application method in which a chemical entity is applied to the lower portions of plant stems or tree trunks just above the soil line.

rdfs:label: chemigation
IAO:0000115: An application method in which a water-soluble chemical is injected into water flowing through an irrigation system.

rdfs:label: contact placement
IAO:0000115: An application method in which a material entity is applied at the time of sowing, and placed in contact with seeds.

rdfs:label: deep placement
IAO:0000115: An application method in which the material entity is placed in the reduced soil layer.

rdfs:label: fertigation
IAO:0000115: An application method in which a water-soluble fertilizer is injected into water flowing through an irrigation system.

rdfs:label: foliar application
IAO:0000115: An application method in which a liquid material entity is sprayed to the leafy portions of a plant.

rdfs:label: plough sole placement
IAO:0000115: An application method in which the material entity is placed in a continuous band on the bottom of the furrow during the process of ploughing. Each band is covered as the next furrow is turned. The aim is to place the material entity in moist soil where it can become more available to growing plants.

rdfs:label: rope-wick application
IAO:0000115: An application method in which a liquid material entity is conveyed from a reservoir to a rope or wick that is wiped into unwanted plants.

rdfs:label: seed dressing
IAO:0000115: An application method in which a material entity is appplied directly on seeds before seeding.

rdfs:label: soil injection
IAO:0000115: An application method in which a material entity is injected under pressure beneath the soil surface.

rdfs:label: tree injection
IAO:0000115: An application method in which a material entity is injected under the bark of trees.

rdfs:label: dibbling
IAO:0000115: An application method in which a material entity is placed into the soil in holes made with a pointed implement.

rdfs:label: drilling
IAO:0000115: An application method in which seeds are uniformlyplaced into shallow furrows before closing the furrows.

rdfs:label: manual irrigation
IAO:0000115: Irrigation method based on manual intervention.

rdfs:label: automatic irrigation
IAO:0000115: Irrigation method with no or just a minimum of manual intervention beside the surveillance. Almost every system can be automated with help of timers, sensors or computers or mechanical appliances.

rdfs:label: hill distribution
IAO:0000115: Planting is done on flat-top circular mounds.

rdfs:label: row distribution
IAO:0000115: Planting is done in lines.

rdfs:label: row on bed distribution
IAO:0000115: Planting distribution where the crop zone and the traffic lanes (wheel tracks or furrows) are distinctly and permanently separated. Soil is moved from the traffic lanes and added to the crop zone, slightly raising the surface level of the crop zone

rdfs:label: uniform distribution
IAO:0000115: Planting is done on all the field surface.

rdfs:label: GenePattern software
IAO:0000115: a software that provides access to more than 100 tools for gene expression analysis, proteomics, SNP analysis and common data processing tasks.

rdfs:label: material area density mesurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Protocol used to measure the area density of a material.

rdfs:label: mulch thickness measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: With a ruler measure the distance between the soil surface and the top of the mulch layer.

rdfs:label: interrow width measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: With a ruler measure the distance between the center of two rows. The center of the rows is where the plant reproductive material has been planted.

rdfs:label: sprout lenght measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Measure the length of sprout with a steel tape.

rdfs:label: water source distance measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Measure the shortest distance between the water source and the entrance of the field with a measuring wheel.

rdfs:label: moisture concentration measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: 1.Weight a sample of the material. 2.Dry this sample. 3.Weight the dry sample. Moisture concentration = ((Ww-Wd)/Ww) x 100 in which : WW = wet weight of the sample, and Wd = weight of the sample after drying.

rdfs:label: bund height measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Measure the distance between the soil surface and the top of a bund. Repeat this operation on multiple bunds, and average the results.

rdfs:label: agricultural process depth measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Measurement protocol in which the depth into the soil of an agricultural process is measured.

rdfs:label: chemical concentration in fertilizer recording protocol
IAO:0000115: Record the concentration of the chemical element of interest in the fertilizer used indicated on the fertilizer container.

rdfs:label: harvested row counting protocol
IAO:0000115: Count the number of row that have been harvested.

rdfs:label: plant density measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Protocol that describes how to count the number of plants in a known area.

rdfs:label: row length mesurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Measure the distance between the beginning and the end of the row.

rdfs:label: lignin concentration measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Protocol in which the lignin concentration of an environmental material is measured.

rdfs:label: determination of organic nitrogen in environmental material protocol
IAO:0000115: Protocol used to determine the content of organic nitrogen in environmental material.

rdfs:label: determination of organic carbon protocol
IAO:0000115: Protocol used to determine the content of organic carbon in environmental material.

rdfs:label: tractor speed recording protocol
IAO:0000115: Record the speed of the tractor in the field.

rdfs:label: mulch color recording protocol
IAO:0000115: Record the color of the mulch applied.

rdfs:label: transplant age counting protocol
IAO:0000115: Protocol in which the age of the transplant is determined by counting the number of days between the seeding date and the transplanting date.

rdfs:label: irrigation equipment depth measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Measure the distance between the soil surface and the top of the irrigation equipment buried in soil.

rdfs:label: well depth measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Tie a small but heavy weight to the end of a piece of string. Lower the weight into the well until it reaches the bottom. Take up the slack and mark the string at ground level. Pull the weight out of the well and measure from the bottom of the weight to the ground level mark. This is the depth of the well.

rdfs:label: pivot lenght measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Measure the lenght of the pivot.

rdfs:label: pest control agent released density recording protocol
IAO:0000115: Record the number of pest control agent released per surface area.

rdfs:label: irrigation water quantity recording protocol
IAO:0000115: Record the quantity of water used for irrigation.

rdfs:label: percolation test protocol
IAO:0000115: Protocol in which the rapidity at which water moves through soil is measured.

rdfs:label: area measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Protocol that describes how to measure a field area.

rdfs:label: soil coverage by environmental material measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Protocol that describes how to measure the percentage of soil coverage by environmental material like mulch or crop residue.

rdfs:label: total quantity of environmental material used compute protocol
IAO:0000115: Add all the quantities of the environmental material of interest applied over a specified period.

rdfs:label: environmental material incorporation percentage measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Protocol that describes how to measure the percentage of incorporation in soil of an environmental material.

rdfs:label: nitrogen recovery efficiency measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Calculate the amount of nitrogen in the crop as a ratio of the amount of nitrogen applied or available.

rdfs:label: nitrogen use efficiency measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Calculate the ratio between the amount of nitrogen fertilizer removed with the crop and the amount of nitrogen fertilizer applied.

rdfs:label: agronomic experimental design
IAO:0000115: A plan specification that states how treatments are allocated to the experimental units during an agronomic trial. It refers to the conceptual framework within which the experiment is conducted.

rdfs:label: intervention design
IAO:0000115: An intervention design is a study design in which a controlled process applied to the subjects (the intervention) serves as the independent variable manipulated by the experimentalist. The treatment (perturbation or intervention) defined can be defined as a combination of values taken by independent variable manipulated by the experimentalists are applied to the recruited subjects assigned (possibly by applying specific methods) to treatment groups. The specificity of intervention design is the fact that independent variables are being manipulated and a response of the biological system is evaluated via response variables as monitored by possibly a series of assays.

rdfs:label: disease state design
IAO:0000115: A study design in which the pathological condition of a part, organ, or system of an organism is studied. The etiology may be from infection, genetic defect, or environmental stress.

rdfs:label: strain comparison design
IAO:0000115: A study design that assays differences between multiple strains, cultivars, serovars, isolates, lines from organisms of a single species.

rdfs:label: dot plot
IAO:0000115: A dot plot is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data where each data point is represented by a single dot placed on coordinates corresponding to data point values in particular dimensions.

rdfs:label: histogram
IAO:0000115:
A histogram is a report graph which is a statistical description of a
distribution in terms of occurrence frequencies of different event classes.

rdfs:label: heatmap
IAO:0000115:
A heatmap is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data
where the values taken by a variable(s) are shown as colors in a
two-dimensional map.

rdfs:label: dendrogram
IAO:0000115:
A dendrogram is a report graph which is a tree diagram
frequently used to illustrate the arrangement of the clusters produced by a
clustering algorithm.

rdfs:label: scatter plot
IAO:0000115: A scatterplot is a graph which uses Cartesian coordinates to display values for two variables for a set of data. The data is displayed as a collection of points, each having the value of one variable determining the position on the horizontal axis and the value of the other variable determining the position on the vertical axis.

rdfs:label: histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to a two-tier grading system
IAO:0000115: A histologic grade for ovarian tumor that is from a two-tier histological classification of tumors.

rdfs:label: histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to the World Health Organization
IAO:0000115: A histologic grade for ovarian tumor that is from a histological classification by the World Health Organization (WHO).

rdfs:label: Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score value specification
IAO:0000115: A performance status value specification designed by the Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group to assess disease progression and its affect on the daily living abilities of the patient.

rdfs:label: Karnofsky score vaue specification
IAO:0000115: A performance status value specification designed for classifying patients 16 years of age or older by their functional impairment.

rdfs:label: fire
IAO:0000115: A fire is a process whereby rapid and exothermic oxidation of a material through a combustion process releases heat, light, and other products.

rdfs:label: acquisition of nutrients from other organism during symbiotic interaction
continuous flood process
IAO:0000115: A bassin irrigation process in which basins are flooded during the entire growing season of plants.

rdfs:label: heat treatment
IAO:0000115: A pest control process in wich extremely hot temperature are used to kill pest.

rdfs:label: cold treatment
IAO:0000115: A pest control process in which extremely cold temperature are used to kill pest.

rdfs:label: flood treatment
IAO:0000115: A mechanical pest control process in which the area being treated against pest is saturated with water at a depth of 15 to 30 cm for a period of 3 to 8 weeks.

rdfs:label: soil solarization treatment
IAO:0000115: A mechanical pest control process in which the soil is covered with a layer of clear or black plastic. The plastic that is covering the ground traps heat energy from the sun and raises the temperature of the soil killing pest.

rdfs:label: fire treatment
IAO:0000115: A mechanical pest control process in which pest or area with pest are directly burned and flamed.

rdfs:label: steam treatment
IAO:0000115: A mechanical pest control process in which steam is used to kill pest.

rdfs:label: diatomaceous earth spreading
IAO:0000115: A mechanical pest process in which diatomaceous earth is used to kill pest. Diatomaceous earth is composed of finely ground skeletons of fossil diatoms. Sharp edges of the ground diatoms scratch the waxy or oily outer layer of soft-bodied insects, which die eventually from dehydration.

rdfs:label: mulching process
IAO:0000115: A planned process in which a layer of material is apply to the soil surface to conserve moisture, improve soil fertility, reduce pests population and enhance the visual appeal of the area.

rdfs:label: using barrier process
IAO:0000115: A mechanical pest exclusion process in which barriers are used to prevent pest from getting into the area to be protected.

rdfs:label: trapping process
IAO:0000115: A mechanical pest removal process in which pests are physically caught.

rdfs:label: hand picking process
IAO:0000115: A mechanical pest removal process in which unwanted organisms are removed by hands.

rdfs:label: water pressure spraying process
IAO:0000115: A mechanical pest removal process in which a forceful stream of water is used to dislodge pests.

rdfs:label: insect vacuuming process
IAO:0000115: A mechanical pest removal process in which a field vacuum is used to suck insects from plants.

rdfs:label: holistic planned grazing
IAO:0000115: Grazing management system developped by Allan Savory. The system is based on a rotational grazing system but doing so at high densities for short intervals. Livestock is used as a tool to increase soil fertility and plant life. Incorporating plant organic matter and manure into the soil promotes the recycling of nutrients.

rdfs:label: mob grazing
IAO:0000115: A grazing management method that involves moving livestock at least daily between small paddocks, sized to match the number of grazing animals, and split by fence. The goal is for every plant in the grazing cell to be either eaten or walked on and trampled. Grass in each paddock then rests for 60-120 days or more.

rdfs:label: strip grazing
IAO:0000115: A system of grazing which confined animals to a strip or small part of the field for rapid grazing in a short time period.. The rest of the field is protected by a temporary fence, usually electric.

rdfs:label: controlled grazing
