IAO:0000115: An intensive rotational grazing system in which livestock is allowed to graze for a limited time, leaving a leafy stubble, and then is moved to another area.

rdfs:label: hohenheim grazing system
IAO:0000115: Intensive grazing system in which the field is divided into many small plots of equal size. Grasses are raised with application of large quantities of nitrogenous fertilizers. The livestock are divided into three groups : high, medium and low yeilders. They are let into the paddock by rotation so that the opportunity for grazing most nutritious immature grasses goes to the high yielders followed by medium producers and lastly low yielders.

rdfs:label: administering substance in vivo
IAO:0000115: A process by which a substance is intentionally given to an organism resulting in exposure of the organism to that substance.

rdfs:label: leave one out cross validation method
IAO:0000115: is a data transformation :  leave-one-out cross-validation (LOOCV) involves using a single observation from the original sample as the validation data, and the remaining observations as the training data. This is repeated such that each observation in the sample is used once as the validation data

rdfs:label: principal components analysis dimensionality reduction
IAO:0000115: A principal components analysis dimensionality reduction is a dimensionality reduction achieved by applying principal components analysis and by keeping low-order principal components and excluding higher-order ones.

rdfs:label: EC 3.5.1.4 (amidase) inhibitor
IAO:0000115: An EC 3.5.1.* (non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of amidase (EC 3.5.1.4).

rdfs:label: mouse metabolite
IAO:0000115: Any mammalian metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in a mouse (Mus musculus).

rdfs:label: human metabolite
IAO:0000115: Any mammalian metabolite  produced during a metabolic reaction in humans (Homo sapiens).

rdfs:label: Daphnia metabolite
IAO:0000115: A crustacean metabolite produced by the genus of small planktonic arthropods, Daphnia

rdfs:label: liter per kilogram
IAO:0000115: A specific volume unit which is equal to one liter volume occupied by one kilogram of a particular substance.

rdfs:label: turns per second
IAO:0000115: A rotational frequency unit which is equal to the number complete turn in a period of time that equals to 1 second.

rdfs:label: increased osmolarity
IAO:0000115: A osmolarity which is relatively high.

rdfs:label: disk harrow
IAO:0000115: An implement that consists of many carbon steel or boron discs, which have many varying concavities and disc blade sizes and spacing and which are arranged into two or four sections. It is used to till the soil where crops are to be planted. It is also used to chop up unwanted weeds or crop remainders.

rdfs:label: elemental molecule
IAO:0000115: A molecule all atoms of which have the same atomic number.

rdfs:label: saline environment
IAO:0000115: An environment which is determined by materials which bear significant concentrations of salts.

rdfs:label: decreased elevation
IAO:0000115: An elevation which is relatively low.

rdfs:label: increased elevation
IAO:0000115: An elevation which is relatively high.

rdfs:label: conventional tillage process
IAO:0000115: A tillage process in which, approximately, less than 15 percent of the soil surface is covered bycrop residue after planting.

rdfs:label: reduced tillage process
IAO:0000115: A tillage process in which between, approximately, 15 to 30 percent of the soil surface is covered by plant residue after planting.

rdfs:label: conservation tillage process
IAO:0000115: A tillage process in which a proportion of plant residue, left over after a harvesting process, is left relatively undisturbed on the tilled land; this is done in order to accomplish several conservation objectives including the maintenance of soil moisture content, the reduction of soil erosion and soil compaction, and/or the reduction of labour intensity and fuel consumption.

rdfs:label: puddling process
IAO:0000115: A tillage process in which saturated or near-saturated soil are worked into soft structureless mud, mainly for paddy rice production.

rdfs:label: chemical pest control implement
IAO:0000115: An implement that is used during a chemical pest control process.

rdfs:label: clod crusher
IAO:0000115: A roller armed with blunt spikes for dragging over newly plowed land to break the clods and render it fit for seeding.

rdfs:label: mouldboard plough
IAO:0000115: An implement that cut, lift and reverse soil with a cutting depth of approximately 15 cm.

rdfs:label: subsoiler
IAO:0000115: An implement that typically has only one thin blade with a sharpened tip, and is used to loosen and break up soil at depths about 30 cm.

rdfs:label: chisel plough
IAO:0000115: An implement that loosen andaerate soil without inverting or turning it.

rdfs:label: ridging plough
IAO:0000115: An implement that is used for plants, such as potatoes or scallions, which are grown buried in ridges of soil. A ridging plough has two mouldboards facing away from each other, cutting a deep furrow on each pass, with high ridges either side.

rdfs:label: spade plough
IAO:0000115: An implement that is designed to cut the soil and turn it on its side, minimizing the damage to the earthworms, soil microorganism, and fungi.

rdfs:label: puddling implement
IAO:0000115: An implement that is used during a puddling process.

rdfs:label: hand plough
IAO:0000115: An object to be used by hand to plough soil.

rdfs:label: paraplough
IAO:0000115: Tool for loosening compacted soil layers 12 to 16 inches (30 to 40 cm) deep and still maintain high surface residue levels.

rdfs:label: cultivator
IAO:0000115: Tillage tool that stirs and pulverizes the soil, either before planting (to aerate the soil and prepare a smooth, loose seedbed) or after the crop has begun growing (to kill weedscontrolled disturbance of the topsoil close to the crop plants kills the surrounding weeds by uprooting them, burying their leaves to disrupt their photosynthesis, or a combination of both). Cultivator is designed to disturb the soil in careful patterns, sparing the crop plants but disrupting the weeds. Cultivator teeth work near the surface.

rdfs:label: seed drill
IAO:0000115: A sowing device that positions seeds in the soil and then covers them. The seed drill sows the seeds at equal distances and proper depth, ensuring that the seeds get covered with soil.

rdfs:label: drum seeder
IAO:0000115: A seeding implement that consists of a seed drum, main shaft, ground wheel, floats, and handle. Joining smaller ends of frustum of cones makes the seed drum.

rdfs:label: hoe
IAO:0000115: An agricultural hand tool ade of a blade set to an handle and used to shape the soil, control weeds, clear soil, and harvest root crops.

rdfs:label: ((13)C)urea
IAO:0000115: A (13)C-modified compound that is urea in which the carbon is present as its (13)C isotope.

rdfs:label: diammonium hydrogen phosphate
IAO:0000115: An inorganic phosphate, being the diammonium salt of phosphoric acid.

rdfs:label: ammonium sulfate
IAO:0000115: An inorganic sulfate salt obtained by reaction of sulfuric acid with two equivalents of ammonia. A high-melting (decomposes above 280degreeC) white solid which is very soluble in water (70.6 g/100 g water at 0degreeC; 103.8 g/100 g water at 100degreeC), it is widely used as a fertilizer for alkaline soils.

rdfs:label: organic anion
IAO:0000115: Any organic ion with a net negative charge.

rdfs:label: polyatomic anion
IAO:0000115: An anion consisting of more than one atom.

rdfs:label: polyatomic cation
IAO:0000115: A cation consisting of more than one atom.

rdfs:label: dinitrogen
IAO:0000115: An elemental molecule consisting of two trivalently-bonded nitrogen atoms.

rdfs:label: ammonia
IAO:0000115: An azane that consists of a single nitrogen atom covelently bonded to three hydrogen atoms.

rdfs:label: hydrogen sulfide
IAO:0000115: A sulfur hydride consisting of a single sulfur atom bonded to two hydrogen atoms. A highly poisonous, flammable gas with a characteristic odour of rotten eggs, it is often produced by bacterial decomposition of organic matter in the absence of oxygen.

rdfs:label: hydrogen chloride
IAO:0000115: A mononuclear parent hydride consisting of covalently bonded hydrogen and chlorine atoms.

rdfs:label: alkali metal molecular entity
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity containing one or more atoms of an alkali metal.

rdfs:label: alkaline earth molecular entity
IAO:0000115: An alkaline earth molecular entity is a molecular entity containing one or more atoms of an alkaline earth metal.

rdfs:label: pnictogen molecular entity
IAO:0000115: A p-block molecular entity containing any pnictogen.

rdfs:label: chalcogen molecular entity
IAO:0000115: Any p-block molecular entity containing a chalcogen.

rdfs:label: cyclic compound
IAO:0000115: Any molecule that consists of a series of atoms joined together to form a ring.

rdfs:label: organic molecule
IAO:0000115: Any molecule that consists of at least one carbon atom as part of the electrically neutral entity.

rdfs:label: salt
IAO:0000115: A salt is an assembly of cations and anions.

rdfs:label: carboacyl group
IAO:0000115: A carboacyl group is a group formed by loss of at least one OH from the carboxy group of a carboxylic acid.

rdfs:label: organodiyl group
IAO:0000115: Any organic substituent group, regardless of functional type, having two free valences at carbon atom(s).

rdfs:label: organyl group
IAO:0000115: Any organic substituent group, regardless of functional type, having one free valence at a carbon atom.

rdfs:label: pnictogen
IAO:0000115: Any p-block element atom that is in group 15 of the periodic table: nitrogen, phosphorus, arsenic, antimony and bismuth.

rdfs:label: chalcogen
IAO:0000115: Any p-block element belonging to the group 16 family of the periodic table.

rdfs:label: coastal wetland
IAO:0000115: A wetland associated with the part of the land adjoining or near a sea or ocean.

rdfs:label: swamp
IAO:0000115: A wetland that features permanent inundation of large areas of land by shallow bodies of water, generally with a substantial number of hummocks, or dry-land protrusions.

rdfs:label: freshwater wetland
IAO:0000115: A wetland whose water that contains low concentrations of salts.

rdfs:label: meadow
IAO:0000115: A habitat of rolling or flat terrain where grasses predominate. Typically, what is called a meadow has more biodiversity than a grassland as the former contains not only grasses but a significant variety of annual, biennial and perennial plants.

rdfs:label: prairie
IAO:0000115: An area of land of low topographic relief that historically supported grasses and herbs, with few trees, and having generally a mesic (moderate or temperate) climate. Dominated by tall grasses (contrast steppe).

rdfs:label: savanna
IAO:0000115: A grassland of the tropics or subtropics with scattered trees.

rdfs:label: steppe
IAO:0000115: A plain without trees (apart from those near rivers and lakes); it is similar to a prairie, although a prairie is generally considered as being dominated by tall grasses, while short grasses are said to be normal in the steppe. It may be semi-desert, or covered with grass or shrubs or both, depending on the season and latitude.

rdfs:label: pasture
IAO:0000115: Grassland used for grazing of ungulate livestock as part of a farm or ranch.

rdfs:label: forest
IAO:0000115: An area with a high density of trees. A small forest may be called a wood.

rdfs:label: desert oasis
IAO:0000115: A small, isolated, fertile or green area in a desert region, usually having a spring or well.

rdfs:label: bone meal
IAO:0000115: A mixture of crushed and coarsely ground bones that is used as an organic fertilizer for plants and formerly in animal feed.

rdfs:label: piece of gravel
IAO:0000115: A piece of rock that is two millimeters (2mm) in its largest dimension (about 1/12 of an inch) and no more than 75 millimeters (about 3 inches).

rdfs:label: manufactured product
IAO:0000115: A material entity that has been processed by humans or their technology in any way, including intermediate products as well as final products.

rdfs:label: terrestrial planet
IAO:0000115: A planet that is composed primarily of silicate rocks or metals.

rdfs:label: gas planet
IAO:0000115: A planet which is primarily composed of hydrogen and helium.

rdfs:label: ocean planet
IAO:0000115: A planet which has a surface layer that nearly completely or completely covered by water, and which has a substantial portion of its mass composed of water.

rdfs:label: ice planet
IAO:0000115: A planet which has a surface layer that nearly completely or completely covered by ice, and which has a substantial portion of its mass composed of ice.

rdfs:label: lava planet
IAO:0000115: A planet which has a surface layer that nearly completely or completely covered by lava, and which has a substantial portion of its mass composed of lava.

rdfs:label: well
IAO:0000115: A cylindrical hole, pit, or tunnel drilled or dug down to a depth from which water, oil, or gas can be pumped or brought to the surface.

rdfs:label: hedge
IAO:0000115: A dense growth of shrubbery planted as a fence or boundary.

rdfs:label: construction
IAO:0000115: A feature that has been constructed by deliberate human effort.

rdfs:label: saline hydrographic feature
IAO:0000115: A geographical feature associated with water with a halinity above 30 ppt (roughly 35 g/L).

rdfs:label: sea beach
IAO:0000115: A landform consisting of loose rock particles such as sand, gravel, shingle, pebbles, cobble, or even shell fragments along the shoreline of a sea.

rdfs:label: lacustrine beach
IAO:0000115: A landform consisting of loose rock particles such as sand, gravel, shingle, pebbles, cobble, or even shell fragments along the shoreline of a lake.

rdfs:label: reef
IAO:0000115: A ridge of rocks, lying near the surface of the sea, which may be visible at low tide, but is usually covered by water.

rdfs:label: levee
IAO:0000115: An artificial slope or wall, usually earthen, which parallels the course of a river, built for the purpose of containing the river.

rdfs:label: shore
IAO:0000115: That part of the land in immediate contact with a body of water including the area between high and low water lines.

rdfs:label: inlet
IAO:0000115: An opening of the sea into the land, or of a lake into its shore.

rdfs:label: bed
IAO:0000115: The portion of the ground surface which lies below water.

rdfs:label: marine pelagic feature
IAO:0000115: A prominent or distinctive aspect, quality, or characteristic of environments occurring within the marine water column.

rdfs:label: irrigation source
IAO:0000115: A water body from which water is taken during an irrigation process and transported to the target of the irrigation process.

rdfs:label: lentic water body
IAO:0000115: A lentic water body is a water body in which the accumulated water, in its totality, has very little to no directed flow.

rdfs:label: lotic water body
IAO:0000115: A lotic water body is a water body in which the accumulated water, in its totality, is flowing.

rdfs:label: river island
IAO:0000115: An island that lies in a river.

rdfs:label: lake island
IAO:0000115: An island that lies in a lake.

rdfs:label: higher-level landform
IAO:0000115: The landform refers to the shape of the land surface in the area in which the agronomic trial site is located.

rdfs:label: agronomic land element
IAO:0000115: Description of the geomorphology of the immediate surroundings of the experimental site.

rdfs:label: desert
IAO:0000115: A region rendered barren or partially barren by environmental extremes, especially by low rainfall.

rdfs:label: elevation
IAO:0000115: A landform elevated above the surrounding area.

rdfs:label: peak
IAO:0000115: The summit of a mount.

rdfs:label: terrace
IAO:0000115: A step-like feature between higher and lower ground: a relatively flat or gently inclined shelf of earth, backed and fronted by steep slopes or manmade detaining walls.

rdfs:label: geological fracture
IAO:0000115: A geological fracture is any separation in a geologic formation, such as a joint or a fault that divides a mass of rock into two or more pieces.

rdfs:label: surface layer
IAO:0000115: A surface layer is the uppermost layer of some material entity.

rdfs:label: atmosphere
IAO:0000115: An atmosphere is a layer of gases surrounding a material body of sufficient mass that is held in place by the gravity of the body.

rdfs:label: aquatic layer
IAO:0000115: A layer in a water mass, itself composed primarily of water.

rdfs:label: boundary layer
IAO:0000115: A boundary layer is a layer of fluid in the immediate vicinity of a bounding surface where the effects of viscosity are significant enough to distort the surrounding non-viscous flow.

rdfs:label: planetary structural layer
IAO:0000115: A planetary structural layer is laminar part of a terrestrial planet or other rocky body large enough to have differentiation by density. Planetary layers have differing physicochemical properties and composition.

rdfs:label: sea coast
IAO:0000115: The general region of indefinite width that extends from the sea inland to the first major change in terrain features.

rdfs:label: atoll
IAO:0000115: An oceanic island, often having a characteristic ring-like shape surrounding a lagoon. Atolls are formed when coral reef grows around a volcanic island that later subsides into the ocean.

rdfs:label: spent mushroom compost
IAO:0000115: A compost that contains the residual compost waste generated by mushroom production. It  generally consists of a combination of wheat straw, dried blood, horse manure and ground chalk, composted together.

rdfs:label: saline water
IAO:0000115: Water which contains a significant concentration of dissolved salts.

rdfs:label: fresh water
IAO:0000115: Water which has a low concentration of dissolved solutes, particularly that of sodium chloride.

rdfs:label: igneous rock
IAO:0000115: Rock formed from molten magma.

rdfs:label: volcanic rock
IAO:0000115: An igneous rock that results from magma reaching the surface either as lava or fragmental ejecta.

rdfs:label: sedimentary rock
IAO:0000115: A rock formed by deposition of either clastic sediments, organic matter, or chemical precipitates (evaporites), followed by compaction of the particulate matter and cementation during diagenesis.

rdfs:label: meristematic cell
IAO:0000115: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) synthesizing protoplasm and producing new cells by division and with only a primary cell wall.

rdfs:label: peripheral zone
IAO:0000115: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) which is the organogenic region of the meristem, characterized by higher rates of cell division.

rdfs:label: shoot system meristem
IAO:0000115: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is part of a shoot system (PO:0009006).

rdfs:label: protoderm
IAO:0000115: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is the outer layer of an apical meristem (PO:0020144), or the outer layer of a plant embryo proper (PO:0000001), and gives rise to a portion of epidermis (PO:0005679).

rdfs:label: apical meristem
IAO:0000115: A maximal portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) located at a shoot apex (PO:0000037) or root tip (PO:0000025).

rdfs:label: primordium
IAO:0000115: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that has as parts protoderm (PO:0006210) and sub-epidermal meristematic tissue and is committed to the development of a particular plant structure (PO:0009011).

rdfs:label: phyllome anlagen
IAO:0000115: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is part of a peripheral zone (PO:0000225) of a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) and will give rise to a phyllome primordium (PO:0025128).

rdfs:label: phyllome
IAO:0000115: A lateral plant organ (PO:0009008) produced by a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148).

rdfs:label: plant ovule
IAO:0000115: A plant organ (PO:0009008) that has as parts a nucellus (PO:0020020) in which a female gametophyte (PO:0025279) is located, one or two integuments (PO:0020021), and a funicle (PO:0020006).

rdfs:label: plant axis
IAO:0000115: An axial plant organ (PO:0009008).

rdfs:label: floral organ
IAO:0000115: A plant organ (PO:0009008) that is part of a flower (PO:0009046).

rdfs:label: shoot system
IAO:0000115: A collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007) that produces shoot-borne portions of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) and the plant structures (PO:0009011) that arise from them.

rdfs:label: collective phyllome structure
IAO:0000115: A collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007) that consists of two or more phyllomes (PO:0006001) originating from the same node or from one or more adjacent nodes with compressed shoot internodes (PO:0005005).

rdfs:label: root system
IAO:0000115: A collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007) that produces root meristems (PO:0006085), the plant structures (PO:0009011) that arise from them and the parts thereof.

rdfs:label: freshwater environment
IAO:0000115: An aquatic environment which is determined by freshwater.

rdfs:label: saline water environment
IAO:0000115: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by saline water.

rdfs:label: non-saline aerosol environment
IAO:0000115: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by an aerosol with a low concentration of dissolved solutes.

rdfs:label: terrestrial biome
IAO:0000115: A biome that applies to the terrestrial realm.

rdfs:label: animal-associated environment
IAO:0000115: An environmental system determined by an animal.

rdfs:label: flat
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a horizontal surface without a slope, tilt, or curvature.

rdfs:label: pot height
IAO:0000115: Distance between the top and the bottom of a pot.

rdfs:label: temperature sensor siting height
IAO:0000115: Distance between the ground and the temperature sensor.

rdfs:label: wind speed sensor siting height
IAO:0000115: Distance between the ground and the wind speed sensor.

rdfs:label: bund height
IAO:0000115: Height of the small earth embankments which contain irrigation water within basins.

rdfs:label: irrigation water quantity
IAO:0000115: Quantity of water applied per irrigation operation.

rdfs:label: tillage tool blade length
IAO:0000115: A length quality which is equal to the length of the tillage tool that penetrate into the soil.

rdfs:label: plot length
IAO:0000115: A length quality that inheres in the smallest unit of an experiment.

rdfs:label: row length
IAO:0000115: A length quality that is the distance between the beginning and the end of a row.

rdfs:label: field maximum length
IAO:0000115: Maximum length of an agromical field.

rdfs:label: center pivot irrigation equipment length
IAO:0000115: Length of the pivot used during the irrigation process.

rdfs:label: well depth
IAO:0000115: Distance between the bottom of the well and the soil surface.

rdfs:label: diameter
IAO:0000115: A length quality which is equal to the length of any straight line segment that passes through the center of a circle and whose endpoints are on the circular boundary.

rdfs:label: mulch thickness
IAO:0000115: A thickness quality which is equal to the distance betwenn the top of the mulch layer to the top of the soil layer.

rdfs:label: plot width
IAO:0000115: A width entity that inheres in the smallest unit of an experiment.

rdfs:label: row width
IAO:0000115: A width entity that inheres in some row.

rdfs:label: field maximum width
IAO:0000115: Maximum width of an agronomical field.

rdfs:label: farm area
IAO:0000115: An area quality inhering in a farm.

rdfs:label: field area
IAO:0000115: An area quality inhering in a field.

rdfs:label: plot area
IAO:0000115: An area quality inhering in a plot.

rdfs:label: harvested surface area
IAO:0000115: Area quality inhering in a surface that have been harvested.

rdfs:label: soil mulch coverage
IAO:0000115: Area of soil covered with mulch.

rdfs:label: soil organic fertilizer coverage
IAO:0000115: Area of soil covered by organic fertilizer.

rdfs:label: porous
IAO:0000115: A porosity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being capable of admitting the passage of gas or liquid through pores or interstices.

rdfs:label: tropical marine condition
IAO:0000115: A tropical marine condition is a tropical condition in which the ocean strongly influences the climate and a wet and dry season occur.

rdfs:label: multi-localised
IAO:0000115: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being confined or restricted to multiple locations.

rdfs:label: stratification
IAO:0000115: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's layered configuration.

rdfs:label: row orientation
IAO:0000115: Orientation of the rows in a field.

rdfs:label: plot orientation
IAO:0000115: Orientation of the plots in a field.

rdfs:label: slope orientation
IAO:0000115: Orientation of the slope

rdfs:label: environmental feature grade
IAO:0000115: The grade of a physical feature, landform or constructed line refers to the tangent of the angle of that surface to the horizontal.

rdfs:label: angle
IAO:0000115: An orientation inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's placement at an angle.

rdfs:label: experimental site altitude
IAO:0000115: Elevation above the sea level of the experimental site.

rdfs:label: weather station altitude
IAO:0000115: Elevation above sea level of the weather station.

rdfs:label: temperature of air
IAO:0000115: The temperature of some air.

rdfs:label: temperature of soil
IAO:0000115: The temperature of some soil.

rdfs:label: temperature of water
IAO:0000115: The temperature of some water.

rdfs:label: liming material area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in liming material by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of liming material applied on a given surface area.

rdfs:label: nitrogen area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in nitrogen by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of nitrogen applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: phosphorus area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in phosphorus by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of phosphorus applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: sulfur area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in sulfur by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of sulfur applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: chemical pest control material area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in chemical pest control material by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of chemical pest control material applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: nitrate area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in nitrate by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of nitrate applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: ammonium area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in ammonium by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of ammonium applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: calcium area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in calcium by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of calcium applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: magnesium area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in magnesium by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of magnesium applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: iron area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in iron by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of iron applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: zinc area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in zinc by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of zinc applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: copper area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in copper by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of copper applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: boron area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in boron by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of boron applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: molybdenum area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in molybdenum by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of molybdenum applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: manganese area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in manganese by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of manganese applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: chlorine area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in chlorine by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of chlorine applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: fertilizer area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in fertilizer by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of fertilizer applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: potassium area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in potassium by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of potassium applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: plant reproductive material area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in plant reproductive material by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of plant reproductive material planted in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: micronutrients area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in micronutrients by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of micronutrients applied in a given surface area. Micronutrients for plants are Boron, Chlorine, Iron, Zinc, Manganese, Molybdenum, Copper, Nikel.

rdfs:label: crop residue area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in above-ground crop residue by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of above-ground crop residue applied in a given surface area.

rdfs:label: rhizobium area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in rhizobium by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of rhizobium inoculated into the soil.

rdfs:label: full-spectrum EM radiation quality
IAO:0000115: An EM radiation quality that is independent of the EM wavelength range.

rdfs:label: optical quality
IAO:0000115: An EM radiation quality in which the EM radiation is within the fiat range of the spectrum visible deemed to be light.

rdfs:label: tractor speed
IAO:0000115: Tractor speed in the field.

rdfs:label: hardness
IAO:0000115: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resistance to pressure, being broken, or pierced

rdfs:label: humidity
IAO:0000115: A quality inhering in air by virtue of the partial pressure exerted by the bearer's water vapour content.

rdfs:label: acidity of soil
IAO:0000115: The acidity of some soil.

rdfs:label: medium acidity
IAO:0000115: A concentration quality inhering in a medium by virtue of the bearer's tendency to hydronate a specific reference base.

rdfs:label: age measurement datum
IAO:0000115: A time measurement datum that is the result of measurement of age of an organism

rdfs:label: adding material objective
IAO:0000115: is the specification of an objective to add a material into a target material. The adding is asymmetric in the sense that the target material largely retains its identity

rdfs:label: cross validation objective
IAO:0000115: A cross validation objective is a data transformation objective in which the aim is to partition a sample of data into subsets such that the analysis is initially performed on a single subset, while the other subset(s) are retained for subsequent use in confirming and validating the initial analysis.

rdfs:label: side dressing
IAO:0000115: A band application in which the material entity is applied after seeding or planting.

rdfs:label: fertilizer basal application
IAO:0000115: A broadcast application in which fertilizer is applied to an area before planting or before seedling emergence.

rdfs:label: top dressing
IAO:0000115: A broadcast application in which a material entity is applied to an area after seedling emergence and establishment of plants.

rdfs:label: material weight per area measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Protocol in which the material is weighed with a scale. The weight of the material is then divided by the surface area over which the material is applied to obtain the area density of the material.

rdfs:label: material volume per area measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Protocol in which the volume of a material is mesured with a graduated container. The volume of the material is then divided by the surface area over which the material is applied to obtain the area density of the material.

rdfs:label: material area density recording
IAO:0000115: Protocol in which the weight or the volume of the material is recorded from the packaging of the material. This value is then divided by the surface area over which the material is applied to obtain the area density of the material.

rdfs:label: agricultural process depth measurement protocol using a penometer
IAO:0000115: Use of a penometer to measure the depth of the agricultural process.

rdfs:label: implement lenght measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Measure the length of the implement that goes into the soil to realize the agricultural process to knoe the depth of the agricultural process. For exemple, measure the length of the tool blade used for tillage to evaluate tillage depth.

rdfs:label: plant density measurement protocol using quadrat
IAO:0000115:
Count the number of plants using a quadrat. A quadrat is a frame of a know area. Set the quadrat on the soil and count the number of plants inside it. Repeat this observation as often as mentioned in your sampling protocol.

Total number of plants= [(total number of plants counted inside the quadrat during all the observations)/ (quadrat area)/(number of observation)]x field size.

rdfs:label: plant density simple measurement protocol
IAO:0000115:
Count the number of plants in a defined area.

Plant density= Total number of plants/ defined area

rdfs:label: lignin concentration measurement protocol using acetylbromide
IAO:0000115: Measure the lignin concentration following the acetylbromide method.

rdfs:label: lignin concentration measurement protocol using acid detergent fiber
IAO:0000115: Measure the lignin concentration following the acid detergent fiber method

rdfs:label: lignin concentration measurement protocol using thioglycolic acid
IAO:0000115: Measure the lignin concentration with the thioglycolic acid method.

rdfs:label: lignin concentration measurement Klason protocol
IAO:0000115: Measure the lignin concentration with the Klason method.

rdfs:label: lignin concentration measurement protocol using permanganate
IAO:0000115: Measure the lignin concentration with the permanganate method.

rdfs:label: lignin concentration measurement protocol using acid detergent lignin
IAO:0000115: Measure the lignin concentration with the acid detergent lignin method.

rdfs:label: kjeldahl method
IAO:0000115: Method for the quantitative determination of organic nitrogen in chemical substance.

rdfs:label: dry combustion method
IAO:0000115: Protocol used to determine organic carbon content in environmental material according to the amount of CO2 released during combustion of the material.

rdfs:label: walkley-black method
IAO:0000115: A determination of organic carbon protocol that uses chromic acid to measure the oxidizable organic carbon in an environmental material.

rdfs:label: area direct measurement
IAO:0000115: Measure the field area in the field.

rdfs:label: area measurement using cartography
IAO:0000115: Measure the field area using a map (paper or electronic format).

rdfs:label: area recording protocol
IAO:0000115: Record the information giving by a person that knows the field area (farmer, field owner).

rdfs:label: soil coverage visual assessment protocol
IAO:0000115: Assess visually the percentage of soil covered by environmental material.

rdfs:label: soil coverage manual measurement protocol
IAO:0000115: Measure the percentage of soil covered by environmental material by counting the environmental material using quadrat, rope with knots or other devices.

rdfs:label: soil coverage measurement using GIS
IAO:0000115: Use GIS to measure the percentage of soil covered by environmental material.

rdfs:label: incorporation percentage visual assessment
IAO:0000115: Assess visually the percentage of environmental material that has been buried into soil during the incorporation process.

rdfs:label: incorporation percentage measurement using GIS
IAO:0000115: Use GIS to measure the percentage of environmental material that has been buried into soil during the incorporation process.

rdfs:label: incorporation percentage manual measurement
IAO:0000115: Measure the percentage of environmental material that has been buried into soil by counting the environmental material using quadrat, rope with knots or other devices befor and after the incorporation process.

rdfs:label: split plot design
IAO:0000115: An experimental design that enables an additional factor or treatment to be included at more than one level; each plot is split into two or more parts.

rdfs:label: strip plot design
IAO:0000115:
An experimental design in which the desired precision for measuring the interaction effect between the two factors is higher than that for measuring the main effect of either one of  the two factors. This is accomplished with the use of three plot sizes : 
1. Vertical strip plot for the first factor  vertical factor 
2. Horizontal strip plot for the second factor  horizontal factor 
3. Interaction plot for the interaction between 2 factors

rdfs:label: factorial design
IAO:0000115: An experimental design in which two or more factors, each with discrete possible values or "levels", and whose experimental units take on all possible combinations of these levels across all such factors. That is, the design provides information on the average effect of the individual factors as well as the interaction between these two factors.

rdfs:label: completely randomized design
IAO:0000115: An experimental design in which the treatments are assigned completely at random so that each experimental unit has the same chance of receiving any one treatment. Any difference among experimental units receiving the same treatment is considered as experimental error. Hence, it is appropriate only for experiments with homogeneous experimental units, such as laboratory experiments, where environmental effects are relatively easy to control.

rdfs:label: lattice design
IAO:0000115: An experimental design in which the blocks should be composed of plots that are as homogeneous as possible. Further, blocks in the same replication should be as near as possible to maximize the variation among replication. These incomplete blocks are combined into groups that form separate, complete replications.

rdfs:label: replicated control design
IAO:0000115: An experimental design in which each treatment is included only once and is near to a control treatment. A control treatment is usually either a common practice or no practice.

rdfs:label: demonstration strip design
IAO:0000115: An experimental design in which basic farming practices are compared using demonstration strips on a farm field. Usually the comparison is between two to four treatments, up to a maximum of 10 and each treatment is included only once.

rdfs:label: randomized complete block design
IAO:0000115: A randomized complete block design is_a study design which assigns randomly treatments to block. The number of units per block equals the number of treatment so each block receives each treatment exactly once (hence the qualifier 'complete'). The design was originally devised from field trials used in agronomy and agriculture. The analysis assumes that there is no interaction between block and treatment. The method was then used in other settings So The randomised complete block design is a design in which the subjects are matched according to a variable which the experimenter wishes to control. The subjects are put into groups (blocks) of the same size as the number of treatments. The members of each block are then randomly assigned to different treatment groups.

rdfs:label: conflagration
IAO:0000115: A fire which occurs in a large spatial area poses a risk to human life, animal life, health, and/or property.

rdfs:label: Daphnia magna metabolite
IAO:0000115: A Daphnia metabolite produced by the species Daphnia magna.

rdfs:label: hard
IAO:0000115: A hardness quality of being rigid and resistant to pressure.

rdfs:label: tandem disc harrow
IAO:0000115: A disk harrow with disc blades arranged into four sections.

rdfs:label: offset disc harrow
IAO:0000115: A disk harrow with disc blades arranged into two sections.

rdfs:label: hydrides
IAO:0000115: Hydrides are chemical compounds of hydrogen with other chemical elements.

rdfs:label: halide
IAO:0000115: Any heteroatomic molecular entity that is a chemical compound of halogen with other chemical elements.

rdfs:label: saline aerosol environment
IAO:0000115: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by a saline aerosol.

rdfs:label: mulch-till
IAO:0000115: A conservation tillage process in which non-inversion tillage tools that partially incorporate surface organic material are used on the entire surface of the field.

rdfs:label: ridge-till
IAO:0000115: A conservation tillage process in which, in a land with permanent ridges, previous crop's residue is cleared off ridge-tops into adjacent furrows to make way for the new crop being planted on ridges.

rdfs:label: strip-till
IAO:0000115: A conservation tillage process in which narrow strips are tilled where seeds will be planted, leaving the soil in between the rows untilled.

rdfs:label: manual oilseed drill
IAO:0000115:
A seed drill that consists of a seed box attached to the mainframe of a hand wheel hoe. A fluted roller assembly is provided at the bottom of the seed box. Fluted roller is rotated with the help of
chain and sprockets from the ground wheel.

rdfs:label: trivalent inorganic anion
IAO:0000115: Any inorganic anion with a valency of three.

rdfs:label: divalent inorganic anion
IAO:0000115: Any inorganic anion with a valency of two.

rdfs:label: monovalent inorganic anion
IAO:0000115: Any inorganic anion with a valency of one.

rdfs:label: monovalent inorganic cation
IAO:0000115: An atom or small molecule with a positive charge that does not contain carbon in covalent linkage, with a valency of one.

rdfs:label: divalent inorganic cation
IAO:0000115: An inorganic cation with a valency of two.

rdfs:label: carboxylic acid anion
IAO:0000115: The conjugate base formed when the carboxy group of a carboxylic acid is deprotonated.

rdfs:label: carbon oxoanion
IAO:0000115: A negative ion consisting solely of carbon and oxygen  atoms, and therefore having the general formula CxOy(n-) for some integers x, y and n.

rdfs:label: ammonium ion
IAO:0000115: Ammonium, NH4(+), and derivatives formed by substitution by univalent groups.

rdfs:label: hydracid
IAO:0000115: A hydracid is a compound which contains hydrogen that is not bound to oxygen, and which produces a conjugate base by loss of positive hydrogen ion(s) (hydrons).

rdfs:label: chlorine molecular entity
IAO:0000115: A halogen molecular entity containing one or more atoms of chlorine.

rdfs:label: organic molecular entity
IAO:0000115: Any molecular entity that contains carbon.

rdfs:label: aromatic compound
IAO:0000115: A cyclically conjugated molecular entity with a stability (due to delocalization) significantly greater than that of a hypothetical localized structure (e.g. Kekule structure) is said to possess aromatic character.

rdfs:label: organic cyclic compound
IAO:0000115: Any organic molecule that consists of atoms connected in the form of a ring.

rdfs:label: organic oxo compound
IAO:0000115: Organic compounds containing an oxygen atom, =O, doubly bonded to carbon or another element.

rdfs:label: imidic acid
IAO:0000115: Compounds derived from oxoacids RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0) by replacing =O by =NR; thus tautomers of amides. In organic chemistry an unspecified imidic acid is generally a carboximidic acid, RC(=NR)(OH).

rdfs:label: onium cation
IAO:0000115: Mononuclear cations derived by addition of a hydron to a mononuclear parent hydride of the pnictogen, chalcogen and halogen families.

rdfs:label: univalent carboacyl group
IAO:0000115: A univalent carboacyl group is a group formed by loss of OH from the carboxy group of a carboxylic acid.

rdfs:label: lagoon
IAO:0000115: A sheet of saline water separated from the open sea by sand or shingle banks. The sheet of water between an offshore reef, especially of coral and mainland. The sheet of water within a ring or horseshoe shaped atoll.

rdfs:label: mangrove swamp
IAO:0000115: An swamp formed of trees and shrubs that grow in saline coastal habitats in the tropics and subtropics.

rdfs:label: dome swamp
IAO:0000115: A dome swamp is a swamp which occurs in a depression where deeper waters at the centre of the swamp allow  trees to grow taller relative to those in shallower regions of the depression. This creates a dome-like shape.

rdfs:label: planted forest
IAO:0000115: A forest that has been intentionally established by human intervention.

rdfs:label: tropical marine semi-evergreen forest
IAO:0000115: A semi-evergreen forest is a forest which undergoes a long dry season and, as a consequence, has a two-storey layer structure,  a dry canopy, a leaf litter layer that only decays during moist periods trees with very small leaves or which shed their leaves to conserve water and which flower during the dry season and grow during the wet season.

rdfs:label: primary forest
IAO:0000115: Forest which originally covered a region before changes in the environment brought about by people. (Source: PHC)

rdfs:label: desert planet
IAO:0000115: A terrestrial planet which has a surface dominated by hot deserts.

rdfs:label: helium planet
IAO:0000115: A gas planet which has an atmosphere composed primarily of helium.

rdfs:label: first-order administrative region
IAO:0000115: A primary administrative division of a country, such as a state in the United States.

rdfs:label: second-order administrative region
IAO:0000115: A subdivision of a first-order administrative division.

rdfs:label: third-order administrative region
IAO:0000115: A subdivision of a second-order administrative division.

rdfs:label: political entity
IAO:0000115: A geographical region whose affairs and population are administered by an authority.

rdfs:label: field margin
IAO:0000115:
Strips of land along the borders of crop fields. It also include vegetative strips adjacent
to roads, paths, railways, hedgerows and forest boundaries.

rdfs:label: farm
IAO:0000115: A tract of crop or grazing land, as well as the group of buildings with and often surrounding a farmhouse, including barns, sheds, and other outbuildings, used for agricultural production.

rdfs:label: plantation
IAO:0000115: An intentional planting of a crop, on a large scale, usually for uses other than cereal production or pasture. The term is currently most often used for plantings of trees and shrubs. The term tends also to be used for plantings maintained on economic bases other than that of subsistence farming.

rdfs:label: sea shore
IAO:0000115: That part of the land in immediate contact with a sea, including the intertidal zone.

rdfs:label: coastal inlet
IAO:0000115: An opening of the sea into the land.

rdfs:label: lake inlet
IAO:0000115: An opening of a lake into its shore.

rdfs:label: lake
IAO:0000115: A body of water or other liquid of considerable size contained on a body of land.

rdfs:label: river
IAO:0000115: A stream which, through permanent or seasonal flow processes, moves from elevated land towards lower elevations through a definite channel and empties either into a sea, lake, or another river or ends on land as bed seepage and evapotranspiration exceed water supply.

rdfs:label: spring
IAO:0000115: A point where groundwater or steam flows out of the ground, and is thus where the aquifer surface meets the ground surface or where there is a fissure.

rdfs:label: marine water body
IAO:0000115: A significant accumulation of water which is part of a marine biome.

rdfs:label: watercourse
IAO:0000115: A flowing body of water.

rdfs:label: mountain
IAO:0000115: A landform that extends above the surrounding terrain in a limited area. A mountain is generally steeper than a hill, but there is no universally accepted standard definition for the height of a mountain or a hill although a mountain usually has an identifiable summit and a local relief of more than 300m.

rdfs:label: hill
IAO:0000115: A rounded elevation of limited extent rising above the surrounding land with local relief of less than 300m.

rdfs:label: plain
IAO:0000115: A region of general uniform slope, comparatively level, and of considerable extent.

rdfs:label: valley
IAO:0000115: A depression which has been formed as a result of erosion by water or ice and which is low-lying, bordered by higher ground, and especially elongate.

rdfs:label: plateau
IAO:0000115: An elevated and comparatively level expanse of land.

rdfs:label: beach
IAO:0000115: A landform consisting of loose rock particles such as sand, gravel, shingle, pebbles, cobble, or even shell fragments along the shoreline of a body of water.

rdfs:label: coral reef
IAO:0000115: Aragonite structures produced by living organisms, found in shallow, marine waters with little nutrients in the water.

rdfs:label: dune
IAO:0000115: A hill of sand built by eolian processes.

rdfs:label: ridge
IAO:0000115: A long and narrow upland with steep sides.

rdfs:label: depression
IAO:0000115: A landform sunken or depressed below the surrounding area.

rdfs:label: interfluve
IAO:0000115: A relatively undissected upland between adjacent stream valleys.

rdfs:label: slope
IAO:0000115: The part of an elevation or depression between the relatively flat surrounding area and the peak of a mount or the bottom of a depression.

rdfs:label: butte
IAO:0000115: An isolated hill with steep sides and a small flat top, smaller than mesas and plateaus. Buttes are formed by erosion when a cap of hard rock, usually of volcanic origin, covers a layer of softer rock that is easily worn away. This hard rock avoids erosion while the rock around it wears down.

rdfs:label: mount
IAO:0000115: A mountain or a hill.

rdfs:label: kame
IAO:0000115: An irregularly shaped hill or mound composed of sorted or stratified sand and gravel that is deposited in contact with the glacial ice. It can have an irregular shape. Kames are often associated with kettles, and this is referred to as kame and kettle topography. When the ice retreats further, the delta kame often collapses. Kame terraces are frequently found along the side of a glacial valley and are the deposits of meltwater streams flowing between the ice and the adjacent valley side.

rdfs:label: kame terrace
IAO:0000115: A terrace associated with a kame.

rdfs:label: planetary surface
IAO:0000115: A planetary surface is a surface layer where the solid or liquid material of a planet comes into contact with atmosphere or outer space.

rdfs:label: planetary crust
IAO:0000115: A planetary crust is the outermost solid shell of a rocky planet or natural satellite, which is chemically distinct from the underlying mantle.

rdfs:label: sea water
IAO:0000115: Water which has physicochemical properties that have been determined by the processes occuring in a sea or ocean.

rdfs:label: shoot apical meristem
IAO:0000115: A shoot system meristem (PO:0006079) formed at the apex of the shoot axis (PO:0025029), including those originating from an axillary bud meristem (PO:0000232).

rdfs:label: phyllome primordium
IAO:0000115: A primordium (PO:0025127) that develops from a phyllome anlagen (PO:0025430) and is part of a shoot apex (PO:0000037) and is committed to the development of a phyllome (PO:0006001).

rdfs:label: floral organ primordium
IAO:0000115: A primordium (PO:0025127) that is committed to the development of a floral organ (PO:0025395) and is part of a reproductive shoot apex (PO:0025222).

rdfs:label: leaf
IAO:0000115: A phyllome (PO:0006001) that is not associated with a reproductive structure.

rdfs:label: shoot axis
IAO:0000115: A plant axis (PO:0025004) that is part of a shoot system (PO:0009006).

rdfs:label: bud
IAO:0000115: An undeveloped shoot system (PO:0009006).

rdfs:label: shoot-borne shoot system
IAO:0000115: A shoot system that is initiated from a shoot.

rdfs:label: reproductive shoot system
IAO:0000115: A shoot system (PO:0009006) in the sporophytic phase that has as part at least one sporangium (PO:0025094).

rdfs:label: gynoecium
IAO:0000115: A collective phyllome structure (PO:0025023) composed all of the carpels (PO:0009030) in a flower (PO:0009046).

rdfs:label: sea water environment
IAO:0000115: An environmental system determined by seawater.

rdfs:label: desert biome
IAO:0000115: A desert biome is a terrestrial biome which loses more liquid water by evapotranspiration than is supplied by precipitation and includes communities adapted to these conditions.

rdfs:label: mangrove biome
IAO:0000115: A mangrove biome is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its spatial extent, mangrove plants (Rhizophoraceae). Mangrove plants are able to withstand high levels of salinity as well as regions of anoxia and frequent tidal inundation. Mangrove biomes often occur near tropical and sub-tropical estuaries and depositional marine coastal environments where fine sediments (often with high organic content) collect in areas protected from high energy wave action.

rdfs:label: marine biome
IAO:0000115: An aquatic biome that comprises systems of open-ocean and unprotected coastal habitats, characterized by exposure to wave action, tidal fluctuation, and ocean currents as well as systems that largely resemble these. Water in the marine biome is generally within the salinity range of seawater: 30 to 38 ppt.

rdfs:label: stratified
IAO:0000115: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a layered configuration.

rdfs:label: fertilizer area density over a cropping season
IAO:0000115: Total quantity of fertilizer applied in a given surface area during a cropping season.

rdfs:label: seeding area density
IAO:0000115: An area density quality which inheres in seeds by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of the seeds sown on a given surface area.

rdfs:label: radiation reflective quality
IAO:0000115: A scalar EM radiation quality which obtains by the capacity of the bearer to scatter or reflect radiation.

rdfs:label: mulch color
IAO:0000115: A color quality inhering in mulch.

rdfs:label: color
IAO:0000115: A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.

rdfs:label: opacity
IAO:0000115: An optical quality which obtains by virtue of the ability of the bearer to absorb visible light.

rdfs:label: age since planting measurement datum
IAO:0000115: An age measurement datum that is the result of the measurement of the age of an organism since planting, the process of placing a plant in media (e.g. soil) to allow it to grow, which excludes sowing.

rdfs:label: age since germination measurement datum
IAO:0000115: An age measurement datum that is the result of the measurement of the age of an organism since germination, the process consisting of physiological and developmental changes by a seed, spore, pollen grain (microspore), or zygote that occur after release from dormancy, and encompassing events prior to and including the first visible indications of growth.

rdfs:label: age since sowing measurement datum
IAO:0000115: An age measurement datum that is the result of the measurement of the age of an organism since sowing, the process of placing a seed or spore in some media with the intention to invoke germination.

rdfs:label: square lattice design
IAO:0000115: A lattice design in which the number of treatment must be a perfect square. Blocks per replicate and plots per block are equal, and are the square root of the number of treatments.

rdfs:label: alpha lattice design
IAO:0000115: A lattice design that is a resolvable incomplete block design where the number of treatments or block size does not meet the strict requirements for one of the lattice designs. Also the number of entries is a multiple of block size.

rdfs:label: latin square design
IAO:0000115: Latin square design is_a study design which allows in its simpler form controlling 2 levels of nuisance variables (also known as blocking variables).he 2 nuisance factors are divided into a tabular grid with the property that each row and each column receive each treatment exactly once.

rdfs:label: water
IAO:0000115: An oxygen hydride consisting of an oxygen atom that is covalently bonded to two hydrogen atoms.

rdfs:label: hydroxides
IAO:0000115: Hydroxides are chemical compounds containing a hydroxy group or salts containing hydroxide (OH(-)).

rdfs:label: oxide
IAO:0000115: An oxide is a chemical compound of oxygen with other chemical elements.

rdfs:label: artificial lake
IAO:0000115: A lake purposefully constructed.

rdfs:label: ammonium
IAO:0000115: An onium cation obtained by protonation of ammonia.

rdfs:label: hydridonitrate(2-)
IAO:0000115: A divalent inorganic anion resulting from the removal of two protons from ammonia.

rdfs:label: azane
IAO:0000115: Saturated acyclic nitrogen hydrides having the general formula NnHn+2.

rdfs:label: phosphate ion
IAO:0000115: A phosphorus oxoanion that is the conjugate base of phosphoric acid.

rdfs:label: sulfide(2-)
IAO:0000115: A divalent inorganic anion obtained by removal of both protons from hydrogen sulfide.

rdfs:label: halide anion
IAO:0000115: A monoatomic monoanion resulting from the addition of an electron to any halogen atom.

rdfs:label: divalent metal cation
IAO:0000115: A metal cation with a valence of two.

rdfs:label: potassium(1+)
IAO:0000115: A monoatomic monocation obtained from potassium.

rdfs:label: hydrogencarbonate
IAO:0000115: The carbon oxoanion resulting from the removal of a proton from carbonic acid.

rdfs:label: potassium salt
IAO:0000115: Any alkali metal salt having potassium(1+) as the cation.

rdfs:label: amide
IAO:0000115: An amide is a derivative of an oxoacid RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0) in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group.

rdfs:label: ammonium compound
IAO:0000115: Compounds (NH4(+))Y(-) and derivatives, in which one or more of the hydrogens bonded to nitrogen have been replaced with univalent groups.

rdfs:label: reactive nitrogen species
IAO:0000115: A family of nitrogen molecular entities which are highly reactive and derived from nitric oxide (.NO) and superoxide (O2.(-)) produced via the enzymatic activity of inducible nitric oxide synthase 2 (NOS2) and NADPH oxidase respectively.

rdfs:label: organooxygen compound
IAO:0000115: An organochalcogen compound containing at least one carbon-oxygen bond.

rdfs:label: heteroorganic entity
IAO:0000115: A heteroorganic entity is an organic molecular entity in which carbon atoms or organic groups are bonded directly to one or more heteroatoms.

rdfs:label: one-carbon compound
IAO:0000115: An organic molecular entity containing a single carbon atom (C1).

rdfs:label: organic acid
IAO:0000115: Any organic molecular entity that is acidic and contains carbon in covalent linkage.

rdfs:label: carbonyl compound
IAO:0000115: Any compound containing the carbonyl group, C=O. The term is commonly used in the restricted sense of aldehydes and ketones, although it actually includes carboxylic acids and derivatives.

rdfs:label: carbamoyl group
IAO:0000115: The univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of -OH from the carboxy group of carbamic acid.

rdfs:label: iron atom
IAO:0000115: An iron group element atom that has atomic number 26.

rdfs:label: national geopolitical entity
IAO:0000115: A political association with effective dominion over a geographic area.

rdfs:label: sound
IAO:0000115: A large sea or ocean inlet larger than a bay, deeper than a bight, wider than a fjord, or it may identify a narrow sea or ocean channel between two bodies of land.

rdfs:label: saline lake
IAO:0000115: A lake whose water contains a considerable concentration of dissolved salts.

rdfs:label: natural lake
IAO:0000115: A lake which has formed as the result of processes that are not or are only minimally driven by human activity.

rdfs:label: crater lake
IAO:0000115: A lake contained within a crater.

rdfs:label: freshwater river
IAO:0000115: A river where fresh water flows.

rdfs:label: ocean
IAO:0000115: Continuous saline-water bodies that surround the continents and fill the Earth's great depressions.

rdfs:label: sea
IAO:0000115: A large expanse of saline water usually connected with an ocean.

rdfs:label: coastal water body
IAO:0000115: Coastal water is a marine water body bordering a coast.

rdfs:label: stream
IAO:0000115: Linear body of water flowing on the Earth's surface.

rdfs:label: coastal plain
IAO:0000115: An area of flat, low-lying land adjacent to a coast and separated from the interior by other features.

rdfs:label: flood plain
IAO:0000115: An area which is subject to periodic flooding.

rdfs:label: sandur
IAO:0000115: The plain formed by the large amounts of silt and sediment, picked up as a glacier erodes the underlying rocks as it moves slowly downhill, and at the snout of the glacier, meltwater can carry this sediment away from the glacier and deposit it on a broad plain. The material in the outwash plain is often size-sorted by the water runoff of the melting glacier with the finest materials, like silt, being the most distantly re-deposited, whereas larger boulders are the closest to the original terminus of the glacier.

rdfs:label: stream valley
IAO:0000115: A valley that contains, and has been formed by, a stream.

rdfs:label: glacial valley
IAO:0000115: A valley that contains, or contained, a glacier and was formed by glacial activity. Typically U-shaped in cross-section.

rdfs:label: beach ridge
IAO:0000115: A ridge of sand just inland and parallel to the beach, usually in series.

rdfs:label: drainage basin
IAO:0000115: An extent or area of land where surface water from rain and melting snow or ice converges to a single point at lower elevation, usually the exit of the basin, where the waters join another waterbody.

rdfs:label: kettle
IAO:0000115: A fluvioglacial landform occurring as the result of blocks of ice calving from the front of a receding glacier and becoming partially to wholly buried by glacial outwash. Glacial outwash is generated when sediment laden streams of meltwater flow away from the glacier and are deposited to form broad outwash plains called sandurs. When the ice blocks melt, holes are left in the sandur.

rdfs:label: channel of a watercourse
IAO:0000115: The physical confine of a river, slough or ocean strait consisting of a bed and banks.

rdfs:label: crater
IAO:0000115: A generally circular saucer or bowl-shaped depression caused by volcanic or meteorite explosive action.

rdfs:label: geographic basin
IAO:0000115: A depression which is part of a planetary crust, is of geographic scale, and is partially or completely enclosed.

rdfs:label: bank
IAO:0000115: The sloping margin of a watercourse, serving to confine it to its natural channel.

rdfs:label: escarpment
IAO:0000115: A transition zone between different physiogeographic provinces that involves an elevation differential, often involving high cliffs. Most commonly a transition from one series of sedimentary rocks to another series of a different age and composition. In such cases, the escarpment usually represents the line of erosional loss of the newer rock over the older.

rdfs:label: rocky slope
IAO:0000115: A rocky slope is a slope which has a surface primarily composed of rock.

rdfs:label: gravelly slope
IAO:0000115: A gravelly slope is a slope which has a surface primarily composed of gravel.

rdfs:label: hillside
IAO:0000115: A hillside is a slope that is part of a hill.

rdfs:label: talus slope
IAO:0000115: A talus slope is a slope which has a surface layer composed of scree.

rdfs:label: land
IAO:0000115: Land is a planetary surface that is not covered by liquid.

rdfs:label: coastal sea water
IAO:0000115: Coastal sea water is sea water that is adjacent to a coast.

rdfs:label: reproductive shoot apical meristem
IAO:0000115: A shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) that gives rise to the apical growth of reproductive tissues and organs.

rdfs:label: ovule primordium
IAO:0000115: A floral structure primordium (PO:0025477) that is committed to the development of an ovule (PO:0020003).

rdfs:label: gynoecium primordium
IAO:0000115: A floral structure primordium (PO:0025477) that is committed to the development of a gynoecium (PO:0009062).

rdfs:label: shoot apex
IAO:0000115: A shoot axis (PO:0025029) that is the most distal part of a shoot system (PO:0009006) and has as parts a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) and the youngest primordia (PO:0025127).

rdfs:label: stem
IAO:0000115: A shoot axis (PO:0025029) that is the primary axis of a plant.

rdfs:label: axillary bud
IAO:0000115: A bud (PO:0000055) that develops from an axillary bud meristem (PO:0000232).

rdfs:label: axillary shoot system
IAO:0000115: A shoot-borne shoot system (PO:0004545) that develops from an axillary bud (PO:0004709).

rdfs:label: flower
IAO:0000115: A determinate reproductive shoot system (PO:0025082) that has as part at least one carpel (PO:0009030) or at least one stamen (PO:0009029) and does not contain any other determinate shoot system (PO:0009006) as a part.

rdfs:label: albedo
IAO:0000115: A reflective quality restricted to a particular wavelength.

rdfs:label: black
IAO:0000115: A color that lacks any hues as parts.

rdfs:label: white
IAO:0000115: An achromatic color of maximum brightness; the color of objects that reflect nearly all light of all visible wavelengths.

rdfs:label: yellow
IAO:0000115: A color hue with medium wavelength of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between orange and green, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 570 to 590 nanometers.

rdfs:label: grey
IAO:0000115: A color between white and black colors.

rdfs:label: brown
IAO:0000115: A color consisting of dark orange, red, of very low intensity.

rdfs:label: transparent
IAO:0000115: A optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking opacity.

rdfs:label: opaque
IAO:0000115: A optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's not being clear; not transmitting or reflecting light or radiant energy.

rdfs:label: sulfate
IAO:0000115: A sulfur oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of both OH groups of sulfuric acid.

rdfs:label: potassium chloride
IAO:0000115: A metal chloride salt with a K(+) counterion.

rdfs:label: oxoanion
IAO:0000115: An oxoanion is an anion derived from an oxoacid by loss of hydron(s) bound to oxygen.

rdfs:label: organochalcogen compound
IAO:0000115: An organochalcogen compound is a compound containing at least one carbon-chalcogen bond.

rdfs:label: oxoacid
IAO:0000115: A compound which contains oxygen, at least one other element, and at least one hydrogen bound to oxygen, and which produces a conjugate base by loss of positive hydrogen ion(s) (hydrons).

rdfs:label: phosphate(3-)
IAO:0000115: A phosphate ion that is the conjugate base of hydrogenphosphate.

rdfs:label: hydrogenphosphate
IAO:0000115: A phosphate ion that is the conjugate base of dihydrogenphosphate.

rdfs:label: nitrate
IAO:0000115: A nitrogen oxoanion formed by loss of a proton from nitric acid. Principal species present at pH 7.3.

rdfs:label: dihydrogenphosphate
IAO:0000115: A monovalent inorganic anion that consists of phosphoric acid in which one of the three OH groups has been deprotonated.

rdfs:label: chloride
IAO:0000115: A halide anion formed when chlorine picks up an electron to form an an anion.

rdfs:label: organonitrogen compound
IAO:0000115: Any heteroorganic entity containing at least one carbon-nitrogen bond.

rdfs:label: reservoir
IAO:0000115: An artificial body of water, often contained by a dam, constructed for the purpose of water storage.

rdfs:label: potassium nitrate
IAO:0000115: The inorganic nitrate salt of potassium.

rdfs:label: calcium nitrate
IAO:0000115: Inorganic nitrate salt of calcium.

rdfs:label: primary amide
IAO:0000115: A derivative of an oxoacid RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0) in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group.

rdfs:label: sulfuric acid
IAO:0000115: A sulfur oxoacid that consits of two oxo and two hydroxy groups joined covalently to a central sulfur atom.

rdfs:label: phenylpropanoid
IAO:0000115: Any organic aromatic compound with a structure based on a phenylpropane skeleton. The class includes naturally occurring phenylpropanoid esters, flavonoids, anthocyanins, coumarins and many small phenolic molecules as well as their semi-synthetic and synthetic analogues. Phenylpropanoids are also precursors of lignin.

rdfs:label: phosphate
IAO:0000115: Salts and esters of phosphoric and oligophosphoric acids and their chalcogen analogues. In inorganic chemistry, the term is also used to describe anionic coordination entities with phosphorus as central atom.

rdfs:label: hanging valley
IAO:0000115: A tributary valley with the floor at a higher relief than the main channel into which it flows. They are most commonly associated with U-shaped valleys when a tributary glacier flows into a glacier of larger volume.

rdfs:label: stream bank
IAO:0000115: The sloping margin of a stream, serving to confine it to its natural channel.

rdfs:label: flower meristem
IAO:0000115: A portion of reproductive shoot apical meristem tissue (PO:0008028) that gives rise to the floral organs (PO:0025395).

rdfs:label: reproductive shoot apex
IAO:0000115: A shoot apex that has as part a reproductive shoot apical meristem.

rdfs:label: basal axillary shoot system
IAO:0000115: An axillary shoot system (PO:0006343) that is part of a stem base (PO:0008039).

rdfs:label: light yellow
IAO:0000115: A color consisting of yellow hue and high brightness.

rdfs:label: ammonium hydroxide
IAO:0000115: A solution of ammonia in water.

rdfs:label: carbamic acid
IAO:0000115: A one-carbon compound that is ammonia in which one of the hydrogens is replaced by a carboxy group. Although carbamic acid derivatives are common, carbamic acid itself has never been synthesised.

rdfs:label: carboxamide
IAO:0000115: An amide of a carboxylic acid, having the structure RC(=O)NR2. The term is used as a suffix in systematic name formation to denote the -C(=O)NH2 group including its carbon atom.

rdfs:label: organic amino compound
IAO:0000115: A compound formally derived from ammonia by replacing one, two or three hydrogen atoms by organyl groups.

rdfs:label: sulfates
IAO:0000115: Salts and esters of sulfuric acid

rdfs:label: irrigation reservoir
IAO:0000115: A reservoir constructed for the purpose of providing water for irrigation.

rdfs:label: ammonium dihydrogen phosphate
IAO:0000115: The ammonium salt of phosphoric acid (molar ratio 1:1).

rdfs:label: river bank
IAO:0000115: The sloping margin of a river, serving to confine it to its natural channel.

rdfs:label: phosphorus oxoacid
IAO:0000115: A pnictogen oxoacid which contains phosphorus and oxygen, at least one hydrogen atom bound to oxygen, and forms an ion by the loss of one or more protons.

rdfs:label: carboxylic acid
IAO:0000115: A carbon oxoacid acid carrying at least one -C(=O)OH group and having the structure RC(=O)OH, where R is any any monovalent functional group. Carboxylic acids are the most common type of organic acid.

rdfs:label: isourea
IAO:0000115: A carboximidic acid that is the imidic acid tautomer of urea, H2NC(=NH)OH, and its hydrocarbyl derivatives.

rdfs:label: monocarboxylic acid amide
IAO:0000115: A carboxamide derived from a monocarboxylic acid.

rdfs:label: lignin
IAO:0000115: A polyphenylpropanoid derived from three monolignol monomers: trans-p-coumaryl alcohol, coniferol and trans-sinapyl alcohol. There is extensive cross-linking and no defined primary structure.

rdfs:label: nitric acid
IAO:0000115: A nitrogen oxoacid of formula HNO3 in which the nitrogen atom is bonded to a hydroxy group and by equivalent bonds to the remaining two oxygen atoms.

rdfs:label: phosphoric acids
IAO:0000115: Compounds containing one or more phosphoric acid units.

rdfs:label: urea
IAO:0000115: A carbonyl group with two C-bound amine groups.

rdfs:label: amino acid
IAO:0000115: A carboxylic acid containing one or more amino groups.

rdfs:label: phosphoric acid
IAO:0000115: A phosphorus oxoacid that consits of one oxo and three hydroxy groups joined covalently to a central phosphorus atom.
